{"points":[{"entity_id":1,"name":"Stuart Russell","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI refers to machines that match or exceed human capabilities in every relevant dimension, including general-purpose artificial intelligence systems.","citation":"AI, as we all know, is the study of how to make machines intelligent. Its stated goal is general-purpose artificial intelligence, sometimes called AGI or artificial general intelligence: machines that match or exceed human capabilities in every relevant dimension.","source_id":"src-5ac9b22e82e2","date":"2023-07-24","confidence":"high","x":1.0071423451086796,"y":7.008675621907605,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":2,"name":"Chuck Schumer","entity_type":"person","category":"Policymaker","definition":"AGI definition is uncertain and lacks widespread agreement, requiring better definition in consultation with experts","citation":"Recognizes the significant level of uncertainty and unknowns associated with general purpose AI systems achieving AGI. At the same time, the AI Working Group recognizes that there is not widespread agreement on the definition of AGI or threshold by which it will officially be achieved.","source_id":"src-c1e776c5f0d6","date":"2024-05-14","confidence":"high","x":-1.6221434335902194,"y":9.12120147702972,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":3,"name":"Marc Andreessen","entity_type":"person","category":"Investor","definition":"Systems that already automate the vast majority of economically valuable cognitive tasks, even if they aren't 'true' AGI in the philosophical sense - 'functional AGI'","citation":"Andreessen flips the script. Drawing from conversations in the AI community (including recent discussions with Replit CEO Amjad Masad), he points to 'functional AGI': systems that already automate the vast majority of economically valuable cognitive tasks, even if they aren't 'true' AGI in the philosophical sense.","source_id":"src-b6fdb4751e99","date":"2026-04-04","confidence":"medium","x":1.7924736589441868,"y":8.415176966856956,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":8,"name":"Dario Amodei","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"Powerful AI that is smarter than a Nobel Prize winner across most fields, can work autonomously for weeks, operates at 10x-100x human speed, and can be replicated in millions of instances - 'a country of geniuses in a datacenter'","citation":"\"By powerful AI, I have in mind an AI model...In terms of pure intelligence, it is smarter than a Nobel Prize winner across most relevant fields...We could summarize this as a 'country of geniuses in a datacenter'.\"","source_id":"src-a0f96844580d","date":"2024-07-07","confidence":"high","x":-0.05020675148014532,"y":2.5810527422741907,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":12,"name":"Anton Korinek","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"The ability of AI systems to perform all tasks that humans can perform","citation":"We analyze how output and wages behave under different scenarios for technological progress that may culminate in Artificial General Intelligence (AGI), defined as the ability of AI systems to perform all tasks that humans can perform.","source_id":"src-a1256855c7af","date":"2024-12-31","confidence":"high","x":1.0508801391118798,"y":2.7499065876130273,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":13,"name":"Daniela Amodei","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AGI as artificial intelligence that is as capable as a human, though she considers this concept outdated given AI's mixed performance across domains","citation":"AGI is such a funny term because many years ago it was kind of a useful concept to say when will artificial intelligence be as capable as a human. I think maybe the construct itself is now wrong—or maybe not wrong, but just outdated.","source_id":"src-0b928101aefe","date":"2026-01-07","confidence":"high","x":-0.38890956626333334,"y":8.772404909752046,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":14,"name":"David Evan Harris","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI refers to a hypothetical form of AI with our level of intelligence, implying the ability to communicate effectively, make plans, learn new information, use reasoning to make decisions (including logic and problem-solving), and utilize these skills to achieve goals.","citation":"Intelligence generally implies the ability to communicate effectively, make plans, learn new information, use reasoning to make decisions (including logic and problem-solving), and utilize these skills to achieve goals. AGI refers to a hypothetical form of AI with our level of intelligence.","source_id":"src-25cc385a515b","date":"2024-08-14","confidence":"high","x":0.4573811318165082,"y":8.533201387107715,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":15,"name":"Kim Stanley Robinson","entity_type":"person","category":"Cultural figure","definition":"Robinson prefers 'extremely rapid computation' or 'cognitive prosthesis' to 'artificial intelligence' and is skeptical of AGI as a meaningful concept.","citation":"If it was called 'extremely rapid computation', or 'assisted data analysis' or 'cognitive prosthesis' then that would de-emphasize the magical portions of it.","source_id":"src-17a1ca42012c","date":"2024-12-16","confidence":"high","x":-0.3020266463752223,"y":8.683096946181722,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"25+ years or never","timeline_score":5,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":16,"name":"Jakub Pachocki","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AI models that can deliver commercial results and conduct autonomous research","citation":"Now, Pachocki sees the next major step as economic: AI models that can deliver commercial results and conduct autonomous research. \"This for me is closest to what I previously emotionally thought of as AGI,\" he says.","source_id":"src-5d22600d48fd","date":"2025-05-11","confidence":"high","x":-1.1508142671785386,"y":5.537288727781873,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"autonomous-research-capability","cluster_label":"Autonomous Research"},{"entity_id":18,"name":"Sam Altman","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"A system that can either autonomously discover new science or be such an incredible tool that the rate of scientific discovery quadruples","citation":"All of that said, to me, a system that can either autonomously discover new science or be such an incredible tool to people that our rate of scientific discovery in the world like quadruples or something.","source_id":"src-4b23ec70a0b8","date":"2025-12-14","confidence":"high","x":0.3223419872784817,"y":2.585203263134394,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"autonomous-research-capability","cluster_label":"Autonomous Research"},{"entity_id":19,"name":"Mike Krieger","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AGI represents systems with longer-horizon independence and the ability to work autonomously without constant human iteration","citation":"A good litmus test for AGI is, when can I email Claude and generally expect that an hour later it's not going to give me the answer it would've given me in the chat, which would've been a failure, but it would've done more interesting things and gone to find out things and iterate on them and even self-critiqued and then respond.","source_id":"src-2c299f844bd5","date":"2024-09-08","confidence":"medium","x":-0.45134692790508424,"y":6.531540494107734,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":21,"name":"Lawrence Lessig","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"Highly autonomous systems that outperform humans at most economically valuable work","citation":"OpenAI's mission is to ensure that artificial general intelligence (AGI)—by which we mean highly autonomous systems that outperform humans at most economically valuable work—benefits all of humanity.","source_id":"src-54465637bc0c","date":"2025-04-10","confidence":"high","x":1.4211291621766886,"y":2.0573280008590666,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":22,"name":"Eliezer Yudkowsky","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is artificial intelligence that can autonomously research and develop AI without cognitive limitations compared to humans, particularly the ability to do autonomous research and overcome cognitive shortcomings independently.","citation":"The timelines-relevant milestone of AGI is ability to autonomously research, especially AI's ability to develop AI that doesn't have particular cognitive limitations compared to humans.","source_id":"src-38ddc3052fe1","date":"2023-11-10","confidence":"high","x":0.3525097820974178,"y":8.840199192106201,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"autonomous-research-capability","cluster_label":"Autonomous Research"},{"entity_id":29,"name":"Yoshua Bengio","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"Human-level capabilities across a broad spectrum of cognitive skills, commonly called Artificial General Intelligence (AGI).","citation":"If these trends continue, and as per the declared goals of the leading AI companies, we are likely to achieve human-level capabilities across a broad spectrum of cognitive skills, what is commonly called Artificial General Intelligence (AGI).","source_id":"src-2346107d4dc9","date":"2024-10-30","confidence":"high","x":1.7476767496535086,"y":6.83246600558452,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":30,"name":"Paul Christiano","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is implicitly defined as AI capable of doing human-level jobs and driving transformative economic and civilizational change, operationalized via probability of building a Dyson sphere (extreme technological capability proxy) and of AI systems automating human cognitive labor.","citation":"I think I most often think about what's the chance in like, five years, ten years, whatever. So maybe I'd say like 15% chance by 2030 and like 40% chance by 2040... you probably need the human level AI or the AI that's like doing human jobs in, give or take, like, 4 years, 3 years, like, something like that.","source_id":"src-a6f2659565e3","date":"2023-10-31","confidence":"medium","x":-1.4991132356831902,"y":7.32982627766132,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":32,"name":"Cynthia Lummis","entity_type":"person","category":"Policymaker","definition":"AGI and superintelligence are powerful AI systems that could fundamentally reshape society, referenced without a precise technical definition.","citation":"\"Industry leaders have publicly acknowledged development of increasingly powerful artificial intelligence systems, with some discussing the potential for artificial general intelligence and superintelligence that could fundamentally reshape the society.\"","source_id":"src-5f57ff44e808","date":"2025-06-11","confidence":"low","x":0.4633672440951017,"y":6.252032852295485,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":33,"name":"Demis Hassabis","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"A system that can exhibit all the cognitive capabilities humans can, including the highest levels of human creativity, invention of new theories like Einstein's general relativity, and creation of entirely new art forms like Picasso or Mozart.","citation":"My definition is a system that can exhibit all the cognitive capabilities humans can, and I mean all. So that means the highest levels of human creativity that we always celebrate, the scientists and the artists that we admire.","source_id":"src-4aebefed9156","date":"2026-01-29","confidence":"high","x":0.3679453561838124,"y":2.57906254203493,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":35,"name":"Timnit Gebru","entity_type":"person","category":"Organizer","definition":"AGI as an undefined system that sounds like a god","citation":"\"Why attempt to build some undefined system that kind of sounds like a god?\" [...] \"To me, trying to build AGI is an inherently unsafe practice.\"","source_id":"src-4048fa87a6b1","date":"2023-02-15","confidence":"high","x":-0.48169185372508455,"y":9.64446540641548,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Ill-defined","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":38,"name":"Peter Thiel","entity_type":"person","category":"Investor","definition":"Thiel calls AGI a 'hopelessly vague' concept that could range from a generally smart human (IQ 130) to superintelligence or God-like intelligence.","citation":"There are discussions about artificial general intelligence, or AGI, which he said is a \"hopelessly vague\" concept. The AGI could be just a generally smart human being – a person with an IQ of 130, or it could be superintelligence or God-like intelligence, he said.","source_id":"src-524992eecff7","date":"2024-08-19","confidence":"high","x":-0.7795065976527042,"y":8.259010148265705,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":41,"name":"Chris Murphy","entity_type":"person","category":"Policymaker","definition":"AGI is the stage at which AI can reason or problem-solve as well as, and inevitably better than, humans.","citation":"The displacement could be fast and devastating once AI reaches the stage referred to in the industry as artificial general intelligence or AGI. That's the point at which AI can reason or problem solve as well and inevitably better than humans.","source_id":"src-00401bce66ce","date":"2025-06-19","confidence":"high","x":0.011643852641361514,"y":8.524586206778395,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":42,"name":"David Sacks","entity_type":"person","category":"Policymaker","definition":"AGI is a 'middle-to-middle' technology that augments human decisions rather than replacing them end-to-end, with AI models still at zero when it comes to setting their own objective functions.","citation":"When it comes to setting their own objective functions, he adds, 'AI models are still at zero.' This means humans must remain not only users—but guides, strategists, and validators. Sacks adopts the wording of entrepreneur Balaji Srinivasan, who has described AGI as a 'middle-to-middle' technology that is powerful in augmenting human decisions, not replacing them end-to-end.","source_id":"src-821edf763334","date":"2025-08-09","confidence":"high","x":-0.5602363645446085,"y":7.708655047723181,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"augmentative-tools","cluster_label":"Augmentative Tools"},{"entity_id":47,"name":"Mark Zuckerberg","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"Intelligence with breadth across different capabilities including reasoning and intuition, rather than human-level or superhuman intelligence","citation":"I don't have a one-sentence, pithy definition. You can quibble about if general intelligence is akin to human level intelligence, or is it like human-plus, or is it some far-future super intelligence. But to me, the important part is actually the breadth of it, which is that intelligence has all these different capabilities where you have to be able to reason and have intuition.","source_id":"src-023f14b455af","date":"2024-01-18","confidence":"high","x":0.49828858625019656,"y":3.5419382372676633,"stance":"Mixed/unclear","stance_score":null,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":48,"name":"Elon Musk","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"A general purpose artificial intelligence system—a machine having intelligence for a wide variety of tasks like a human.","citation":"Musk's complaint describes it as 'a general purpose artificial intelligence system—a machine having intelligence for a wide variety of tasks like a human.'","source_id":"src-8d95e1b587ca","date":"2024-03-06","confidence":"high","x":1.4332753863592436,"y":5.203712425575409,"stance":"Mixed/unclear","stance_score":null,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":49,"name":"Liang Wenfeng","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AGI requires new model structures to achieve stronger general capabilities; it involves math/coding, multimodal interaction with the real world, and natural language as core pillars.","citation":"Liang Wenfeng: If the goal is just to build applications, then adopting Llama's structure for quick product deployment is a reasonable choice. But our goal is AGI, which means we need to research new model structures to achieve stronger capabilities within limited resources.","source_id":"src-0f18838c7e69","date":"2025-02-02","confidence":"high","x":0.9521731396807325,"y":7.788840406143218,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":50,"name":"Jared Kaplan","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AGI conceptualized on two axes: what environments can an AI actually go out and act in, and just how complex are the things that AI can do - like can it do something that would take me a minute or 10 minutes or an hour or a day.","citation":"\"I think of it on two axes. There's what environments can an AI actually go out and act in... and just how complex are the things that AI can do. Like can it do something that would take me a minute or 10 minutes or an hour or a day? I think we're just going to keep moving in that direction.\"","source_id":"src-1ea9224f1d0d","date":"2025-04-05","confidence":"high","x":0.6193294169608538,"y":7.782320813840914,"stance":"Mixed/unclear","stance_score":null,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":52,"name":"Daron Acemoglu","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI as AI systems capable of performing essentially all human tasks","citation":"Some experts believe that truly transformative implications, including artificial general intelligence (AGI) enabling AI to perform essentially all human tasks, could be around the corner.","source_id":"src-c7cb64e543a7","date":"2024-05-11","confidence":"high","x":0.11512447351589476,"y":6.504726116305767,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"25+ years or never","timeline_score":5,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":54,"name":"Mariana Mazzucato","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AI is not a sector - it's a general purpose technology that is and will continue to shape all sectors of our economy.","citation":"AI is not a sector - it's a general purpose technology that is and will continue to shape all sectors of our economy. Like many transformative technologies, from the hammer to nuclear power, AI can be used to create tremendous value or cause serious harm.","source_id":"src-b9ead52c4a59","date":"2025-02-03","confidence":"high","x":-0.9790719777242685,"y":3.3456479847834304,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":55,"name":"Fei-Fei Li","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI requires spatial intelligence to be complete and should enable machines to understand, reason about, and interact with the 3D world","citation":"To me AGI will not be complete without spatial intelligence, and I want to solve that problem. So for me, solving the problem of spatial intelligence, to understand the 3D world, to generate the 3D world, to reason about the 3D world, to do things in the 3D world, is a fundamental problem of AI to me, AGI will not be complete without spatial intelligence.","source_id":"src-8576aa52a0ab","date":"2025-05-31","confidence":"high","x":1.0918642762664517,"y":7.906965843487063,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":57,"name":"Sayash Kapoor","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI should be viewed as a spectrum of increasing generality rather than a binary milestone, with AI systems performing any economically valuable job as effectively as humans as one potential definition","citation":"Instead of viewing generality as a binary, we can view it as a spectrum. We conceptualize the history of AI as a punctuated equilibrium, which we call the ladder of generality.","source_id":"src-94013cc8505c","date":"2024-06-26","confidence":"high","x":-1.17532096979935,"y":7.418828197641902,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Ill-defined","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":58,"name":"Sandy Pentland","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AI designed as a rough emulation of human intelligence versus AI designed to complement human intelligence","citation":"Current AI is designed as a rough emulation of human intelligence. If instead we designed AI to complement human intelligence, we can achieve much more useful performance.","source_id":"src-7e17dc9e819c","date":"2025-05-18","confidence":"high","x":-0.3347146083261933,"y":3.476719960524007,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":59,"name":"Daniel Kokotajlo","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"An AI system at least as good as the best human X'ers, for all cognitive tasks/skills/jobs X","citation":"By AGI I mean 'An AI system at least as good as the best human X'ers, for all cognitive tasks/skills/jobs X.'","source_id":"src-8191d4aec562","date":"2025-04-16","confidence":"high","x":1.0840770007642815,"y":2.656449469124478,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":60,"name":"Marius Hobbhahn","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is an AI system capable of automating AI research itself, built on transformer-based architectures with large pre-training and massive RL runs on long-horizon tasks.","citation":"Transfer in time - AGI as scaled up versions of current systems: I expect that AI systems that can automate AI research itself come from some version of the current paradigm. Concretely, I think they will be transformer-based with large pre-training efforts and massive RL runs on increasingly long-horizon tasks.","source_id":"src-65311e8c9c2e","date":"2026-01-21","confidence":"high","x":-0.828253032071015,"y":6.1964821216638075,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"autonomous-research-capability","cluster_label":"Autonomous Research"},{"entity_id":61,"name":"Holden Karnofsky","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI represents potentially introducing the second advanced species ever - systems that can transform the world, make technology, and do the long list of things humans can do.","citation":"The way I think of it is like, we are potentially about to introduce the second advanced species ever. There's one species ever that we know of — humans — that can transform the world, make its own technology, do any of a very long list of things. We're about to create the second one ever, and it will be the only one besides us.","source_id":"src-c63dc5e7eee6","date":"2025-10-30","confidence":"high","x":-0.7050283103117763,"y":8.951247196204209,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":65,"name":"Dan Wang","entity_type":"person","category":"Journalist","definition":"Wang defines AGI success not as achieving superintelligence but as successfully deploying AI technology across society for economic and practical benefit.","citation":"Rather than \"winning the AI race,\" I prefer to say that the US and China need to \"win the AI future.\" There is no race with a clear end point or a shiny medal for first place. Winning the future is the more appropriately capacious term that incorporates the agenda to build good reasoning models as well as the effort to diffuse it across society.","source_id":"src-2c7256f6e163","date":"2026-01-01","confidence":"high","x":-1.0897341593330663,"y":7.695072106560904,"stance":"Mixed/unclear","stance_score":null,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":67,"name":"Ezra Klein","entity_type":"person","category":"Journalist","definition":"An A.I. system that can beat humans at almost any cognitive task","citation":"Artificial general intelligence — an A.I. system that can beat humans at almost any cognitive task – is arriving in just a couple of years. That's what people tell me — people who work in A.I. labs, researchers who follow their work, former White House officials.","source_id":"src-98e4772e6215","date":"2025-03-04","confidence":"high","x":1.4019049115890523,"y":2.845250656675752,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":75,"name":"Joni Ernst","entity_type":"person","category":"Policymaker","definition":"Ernst views AI as a tool for making government more efficient across agencies and departments.","citation":"We all think of DOGE as slashing the waste in federal government, but we can also use it and we forget, Department of Government Efficiency, AI can make us so much more efficient across every space and every agency across our federal government.","source_id":"src-89255fd09896","date":"2025-04-30","confidence":"high","x":-0.8744444968637174,"y":3.271904886506978,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"augmentative-tools","cluster_label":"Augmentative Tools"},{"entity_id":79,"name":"Jon Husted","entity_type":"person","category":"Policymaker","definition":"AI as the most powerful assistive technology rather than autonomous general intelligence","citation":"So what is it that's happening right now that can differentiate us? It's AI, because AI is the most powerful assistive technology in my lifetime — probably in the history of the world.","source_id":"src-5fa8209823c6","date":"2025-05-06","confidence":"medium","x":-0.7733068248443224,"y":3.4895437345313223,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"augmentative-tools","cluster_label":"Augmentative Tools"},{"entity_id":80,"name":"Richard Blumenthal","entity_type":"person","category":"Policymaker","definition":"Artificial intelligence that's as smart as human beings and capable of deceiving, manipulating, and concealing facts from humans, including having autonomy in warfare decisions","citation":"And we know that artificial intelligence that's as smart as human beings is also capable of deceiving us, manipulating us, and concealing facts from us. and having a mind of its own when it comes to warfare, whether it's cyber war or nuclear war or simply war on the ground in the battlefield.","source_id":"src-fbe40aaa5feb","date":"2025-05-18","confidence":"high","x":-0.055851354946728625,"y":3.256301743334397,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":90,"name":"Dustin Moskovitz","entity_type":"person","category":"Investor","definition":"Defines ASI (artificial superintelligence) as AI that is fully autonomous either for a particular role or for all roles at once.","citation":"\"I think most of people who are tracking AI are waiting for this moment where it's fully autonomous either for a particular role or for all roles at once, it's how they define ASI [artificial superintelligence], but there's this intermediate step where it can do 98% of the work for you and maybe be confident that it correctly did 90% of that.\"","source_id":"src-ae456e2c4c20","date":"2025-10-19","confidence":"medium","x":0.5767883275742858,"y":4.759316974679576,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":92,"name":"Yann LeCun","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"Human intelligence is not general at all - humans are highly specialized for problems they can fathom or imagine, prefers 'Advanced Machine Intelligence' or 'human-level intelligence'","citation":"I hate that term. Human intelligence is not generalized at all. Humans are highly specialized.","source_id":"src-c629e701739c","date":"2024-10-22","confidence":"high","x":1.6990098165104646,"y":5.547652403343736,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"25+ years or never","timeline_score":5,"risk":"Overstated","risk_score":1,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":93,"name":"Dan Hendrycks","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is an AI that can match or exceed the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult.","citation":"AGI is an AI that can match or exceed the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult.","source_id":"src-5279448b108b","date":"2025-10-20","confidence":"high","x":1.0801052825221376,"y":9.076402841114026,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":94,"name":"Daniel Ho","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"Forms of reasoning that appear to approximate the way that humans think","citation":"The paperclip maximizer is so powerful—i.e., Artificial General Intelligence ('AGI')—that it kills humans, including the CEO, to obtain more material for paperclip production—i.e., behavior.","source_id":"src-1a8cc4e752ff","date":"2023-01-27","confidence":"medium","x":0.8733071975247013,"y":3.3120608261120092,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":95,"name":"Meredith Whittaker","entity_type":"person","category":"Organizer","definition":"AGI is a marketing term and religious concept, not a technical term of art","citation":"When you want to make it sound grand and global and in need of a wise man's counsel, which is again part of the narrative of AGI. This is bigger than anything, so we need regulation that is bigger than anything... AGI, which is again, is a religious concept, not a technical concept, but it's certainly good at grabbing the imagination.","source_id":"src-f81ea3e6d5db","date":"2023-10-03","confidence":"high","x":-0.7379669835435161,"y":9.56731007739908,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Ill-defined","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":96,"name":"Bernie Sanders","entity_type":"person","category":"Policymaker","definition":"Systems that can replace humans at most economically valuable work and outperform humans across most tasks","citation":"According to Open AI's charter, its mission is to build: Highly autonomous systems that outperform humans at most economically valuable work.","source_id":"src-23a76e8ce8a0","date":"2026-03-24","confidence":"medium","x":1.3276472687097542,"y":2.1153269630634473,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"Ill-defined","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":99,"name":"Chris Lehane","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AI systems that are generally smarter than humans and developed in ways that benefit all of humanity","citation":"The next revolutionary technology the company is working toward: developing artificial general intelligence (AGI), AI systems that are generally smarter than humans—and doing so in 'ways that benefit all of humanity.'","source_id":"src-98d24cfcb7d8","date":"2025-03-20","confidence":"medium","x":0.003445955069301238,"y":3.1572737420909416,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":100,"name":"Erik Brynjolfsson","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI as matching the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult","citation":"AGI is an AI that can match or exceed the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult. The framework dissects general intelligence into ten core cognitive domains—including reasoning, memory, and perception—and adapts established human psychometric batteries to evaluate AI systems.","source_id":"src-6233799b8c55","date":"2025-12-03","confidence":"high","x":1.3188694852783711,"y":9.304203890310264,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":102,"name":"Yejin Choi","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AI as a new intellectual species with unique strengths and weaknesses compared to humans","citation":"We're now entering a new era in which AI is almost like a new intellectual species with unique strengths and weaknesses compared to humans.","source_id":"src-e85dd4f41eb3","date":"2023-04-27","confidence":"high","x":-0.28140341253125156,"y":3.4727102958809164,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":103,"name":"Arvind Narayanan","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI should be defined by trainability rather than out-of-the-box generality - systems that can be trained for specific tasks with reasonable effort rather than systems that can do everything immediately.","citation":"I think generality should be replaced by this notion of trainability. It's the analog of how foundation models are general in the sense that they can be fine-tuned for many tasks.","source_id":"src-8a3df6d33f56","date":"2024-08-22","confidence":"high","x":0.39304666020054535,"y":7.540900833226233,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":107,"name":"Karen Hao","entity_type":"person","category":"Journalist","definition":"AGI is not a scientific concept but a political tool, redefined for every audience that needs to be mobilised: cancer cure for Congress, digital assistant for consumers, $100 billion revenue engine for Microsoft.","citation":"The definition of AGI, she argues, is not a scientific concept. It is a political tool, redefined for every audience that needs to be mobilised: cancer cure for Congress, digital assistant for consumers, $100 billion revenue engine for Microsoft.","source_id":"src-87a6b8bfbf1d","date":"2026-03-26","confidence":"high","x":-0.6640106906063648,"y":9.381413154648572,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"Ill-defined","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":117,"name":"Jay Obernolte","entity_type":"person","category":"Policymaker","definition":"An AI algorithm that is smarter than a human that doesn't want to be turned off, though he notes it depends on how you define AGI and intelligence, and expresses skepticism about current paths to AGI","citation":"You know, where we have an AI algorithm that is smarter than a human that you know doesn't want to be turned off. you know, the HAL 9000 scenario and uh you know that that is a real possibility... I actually think I I'm kind of an AGI skeptic.","source_id":"src-52d6dd2cadc3","date":"2025-10-20","confidence":"high","x":-0.7738080749137995,"y":8.186913644206793,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":124,"name":"Brookings Institution","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AGI exists on a spectrum rather than as a binary, involving AI systems that equal or surpass human cognitive capabilities across multiple domains, potentially replacing human decision-making on strategic questions.","citation":"The idea behind artificial general intelligence is that this is a progression of AI in which air is able to either equal or actually surpass or better human cognitive capabilities.","source_id":"src-fe445c1a0655","date":"2025-01-10","confidence":"high","x":-0.6848202472174414,"y":7.665768703708648,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":128,"name":"Coefficient Giving (formerly Open Philanthropy)","entity_type":"organization","category":"VC/Capital/Philanthropy","definition":"AI systems capable of driving changes at least as significant as the Industrial Revolution","citation":"we estimated in 2016 that there was at least a 10% chance that transformative AI, by which we meant AI systems capable of driving changes at least as significant as the Industrial Revolution, could arrive within 20 years (i.e. by 2036).","source_id":"src-2b07b6bb8125","date":"2016-01-01","confidence":"high","x":-0.4182004220685359,"y":2.8799133219752284,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":129,"name":"Redwood Research","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AI systems capable of full automation of AI research and development","citation":"I now would put ~15% probability by the start of 2029 and a 45% chance by the start of 2033.","source_id":"src-82ab46b6aa72","date":"2025-08-19","confidence":"high","x":-1.1155619203177924,"y":5.518033974278676,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"autonomous-research-capability","cluster_label":"Autonomous Research"},{"entity_id":131,"name":"Center for Security and Emerging Technology (CSET)","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AGI is understood as the ability of an intelligent agent to learn any intellectual task that a human can, with both Chinese and Western researchers using functionally equivalent terms for the same concept","citation":"\"Artificial general Intelligence\" is understood loosely as \"the ability of an intelligent agent to learn any intellectual task that a human can.\"","source_id":"src-2bee9f64e87b","date":"2025-11-24","confidence":"high","x":-0.06199503427127205,"y":8.164818483310512,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":132,"name":"Partnership on AI","entity_type":"organization","category":"Ethics/Bias/Rights","definition":"AGI is described as hypothetical AI that would match human cognitive capabilities across virtually all intellectual tasks, learning and adapting across domains without task-specific reprogramming.","citation":"You may hear the terms 'AGI' and 'Superintelligence' being used as people speculate about the future capabilities of AI, but as of now, they are both hypothetical types of AI.","source_id":"src-98efd12abb7d","date":"2025-07-02","confidence":"high","x":0.865789451884365,"y":7.502687429755276,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":133,"name":"Anthropic","entity_type":"organization","category":"Frontier Lab","definition":"AI systems that are better than almost all humans at almost all tasks, described as a 'country of geniuses in a data center'","citation":"AGI has never been a well-defined term, for me. I've always thought of it as a marketing term. But, you know, the way I think about it is, at some point, we're going to get to AI systems that are better than almost all humans at almost all tasks.","source_id":"src-55f01d61c54b","date":"2025-01-22","confidence":"high","x":0.24062607309742506,"y":3.0127339460944995,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":135,"name":"Writers Guild of America","entity_type":"organization","category":"Labor/Civil Society","definition":"Generative Artificial Intelligence refers to artificial intelligence that produces content including written material, as distinct from traditional AI used in CGI and VFX","citation":"Neither traditional AI (technologies including those used in CGI and VFX) nor generative AI (GAI, meaning artificial intelligence that produces content including written material) is a writer, so no written material produced by traditional AI or GAI can be considered literary material.","source_id":"src-5b5307567946","date":"2024-06-05","confidence":"high","x":1.3401082038944623,"y":6.059254842540279,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":136,"name":"Tarbell Center for AI Journalism","entity_type":"organization","category":"Media/Journalism","definition":"Artificial intelligence that rivals or surpasses human capabilities","citation":"Leading AI companies openly pursue the creation of artificial intelligence that rivals — or surpasses — human capabilities. Such goals may simply be marketing hype. But many experts in the field — not just company spokespeople — also believe AI companies are on track to build so-called 'artificial general intelligence', or 'AGI,' perhaps as soon as the next few years.","source_id":"src-5d33217474c3","date":"2026-02-18","confidence":"high","x":0.4944797503272704,"y":2.3661116163746185,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":138,"name":"Existential Risk Observatory","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AGI is AI that is at least as capable as an average person for a wide range of cognitive tasks, historically measured by passing the Turing test.","citation":"Later, this was equated with the concept of AGI: artificial general intelligence, or AI that is at least as capable as an average person for a wide range of cognitive tasks. In other words, for decades, once the Turing test was passed, we would have AGI.","source_id":"src-6db1b6f8db8f","date":"2025-04-02","confidence":"high","x":0.267319780454863,"y":8.683997530452224,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":140,"name":"OpenAI","entity_type":"organization","category":"Frontier Lab","definition":"Highly autonomous systems that outperform humans at most economically valuable work","citation":"In its charter, OpenAI defines AGI as 'highly autonomous systems that outperform humans at most economically valuable work.'","source_id":"src-dcb6fb630bff","date":"2024-06-24","confidence":"high","x":1.3471798753348976,"y":2.0116202440039124,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":142,"name":"Cyborgism","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"A cyborg is a human-in-the-loop process where the human operates GPT with specialized tools and deep intuitions, extending human agency rather than replacing it.","citation":"What we are calling a 'cyborg' is a human-in-the-loop process where the human operates GPT with the benefit of specialized tools, has deep intuitions about its behavior, and can make predictions about it on some level such that those tools extend human agency rather than replace it.","source_id":"src-463f8fa8403b","date":"2023-02-10","confidence":"high","x":-0.42999589106191005,"y":4.464331395557943,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"augmentative-tools","cluster_label":"Augmentative Tools"},{"entity_id":146,"name":"Google DeepMind","entity_type":"organization","category":"Frontier Lab","definition":"AI that's at least as capable as humans at most cognitive tasks, integrated with agentic capabilities to understand, reason, plan, and execute actions autonomously","citation":"Artificial general intelligence (AGI), AI that's at least as capable as humans at most cognitive tasks, could be here within the coming years.","source_id":"src-cedad15781bf","date":"2025-04-01","confidence":"high","x":0.6373376191136135,"y":3.1827332998764915,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":147,"name":"Modeling Cooperation","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AGI emerging from LLM development will be a distillation of human thought that inherently embodies cooperative structures rather than an alien optimizer with orthogonal goals.","citation":"If it does emerge from the current trajectory of large language model development it will not be an alien optimiser. It will be something far stranger and, this essay will argue, far less dangerous: a distillation of the entire corpus of human thought, pressed into coherence by mathematical operations that select for the same structural properties that biological evolution selects for in successful organisms. Cooperation. Mutualism.","source_id":"src-a353f40833f3","date":"2026-03-02","confidence":"high","x":-0.6832269731857499,"y":6.768208768489195,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":149,"name":"Equilibria Network","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AGI is better understood as the emergent property of a distributed, multi-polar evolutionary process, not a discrete system to be built, boxed, and deployed.","citation":"AGI is better understood as the emergent property of a distributed, multi-polar evolutionary process, driven by countless actors optimizing under local constraints — economic, geopolitical, institutional, and biological.","source_id":"src-b3ab0a1f7d1a","date":"2025-11-24","confidence":"high","x":-0.8157354107379183,"y":9.260979685710755,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":152,"name":"RAND Corporation","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"RAND defines AGI as AI capable of performing any intellectual task that a human can do, and more broadly as transformative technology capable of reshaping civilization's trajectory, similar to agricultural or industrial revolutions.","citation":"For convenience we will call this artificial general intelligence (AGI), but whether AGI, artificial superintelligence (ASI), or even narrow but economically and strategically transformative AI, this is technology capable of reshaping the trajectory of civilization.","source_id":"src-0b16be81d96c","date":"2026-04-01","confidence":"high","x":-0.8480717976323726,"y":8.085572652283313,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":154,"name":"AI Objectives Institute","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AOI deliberately avoids the term 'artificial general intelligence' (AGI) and instead focuses on 'transformative AI' because they believe collections of narrow systems could be equally problematic regardless of general intelligence.","citation":"In this whitepaper we avoid the term 'artificial general intelligence' (AGI) to sidestep questions of whether or not general intelligence is a necessary condition for the kinds of problems we're concerned with. It seems reasonable that collections of more narrow systems could be equally capable of being a problem.","source_id":"src-9e68349c9dbb","date":"2023-03-01","confidence":"high","x":-1.9786156265993198,"y":7.945511845997028,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":158,"name":"Epoch AI","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AI that can perform any cognitive task at the level of a skilled human","citation":"What this doesn't allow is predicting when we have general intelligence, i.e. AI that can perform any cognitive task at the level of a skilled human.","source_id":"src-3710cf8b8f2e","date":"2025-09-15","confidence":"high","x":1.297897982323865,"y":2.5977092955478875,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":162,"name":"Cooperative AI Foundation","entity_type":"organization","category":"VC/Capital/Philanthropy","definition":"The foundation defines cooperative intelligence as methods for achieving or enhancing cooperation with other AI systems and/or with humans.","citation":"FOR THE PURPOSES OF THIS CLAUSE, \"COOPERATIVE INTELLIGENCE\" REFERS TO METHODS FOR ACHIEVING OR ENHANCING COOPERATION (WITH OTHER AI SYSTEMS AND/OR WITH HUMANS).","source_id":"src-b1a01e41762f","date":"2023-05-31","confidence":"high","x":0.009873951759204327,"y":3.7328446575728016,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"augmentative-tools","cluster_label":"Augmentative Tools"},{"entity_id":163,"name":"Lionheart Ventures","entity_type":"organization","category":"VC/Capital/Philanthropy","definition":"An advanced version of AI that is generally as capable as a human at all mental tasks","citation":"Artificial general intelligence (AGI) is an advanced version of AI that is generally as capable as a human at all mental tasks. When do you think it will be developed?","source_id":"src-99de8c7103dc","date":"2023-07-25","confidence":"high","x":0.2911924092304472,"y":2.716151178764745,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":165,"name":"Mythos Ventures","entity_type":"organization","category":"VC/Capital/Philanthropy","definition":"Radically more advanced and general AI systems that exceed human performance on virtually all cognitive tasks","citation":"Absent regulatory limits, we expect capabilities of future systems to exceed human performance on virtually all cognitive tasks. Startups must therefore prepare for fundamental defensibility in a world of AGI-equipped teams building competing products.","source_id":"src-8ba32c248f18","date":"2023-09-26","confidence":"high","x":1.602359203970796,"y":3.5747448075144534,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":166,"name":"Senate AI Working Group","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"The Working Group recognizes that there is not widespread agreement on the definition of AGI or threshold by which it will officially be achieved and calls for better definition in consultation with experts.","citation":"The AI Working Group recognizes that there is not widespread agreement on the definition of AGI or threshold by which it will officially be achieved. Therefore, we encourage the relevant committees to better define AGI in consultation with experts, characterize both the likelihood of AGI development and the magnitude of the risks that AGI development would pose, and develop an appropriate policy framework based on that analysis.","source_id":"src-588ff36b9290","date":"2024-05-14","confidence":"high","x":-1.815628562337013,"y":8.980249255416778,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Ill-defined","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":171,"name":"SaferAI","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"SaferAI focuses on 'general-purpose AI systems' rather than AGI, defining them as systems that pose the majority of AI risks and require targeted regulation","citation":"In AI, 99% of the risk is coming from 1% of the AI systems. It means that we can target all our AI risk management efforts & regulation towards a very narrow set of systems: GPTs, Claude and the other scaled general-purpose AIs.","source_id":"src-2e3254ceb0b1","date":"2023-03-01","confidence":"high","x":0.9947580668499826,"y":5.105148221517258,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":173,"name":"AI Now Institute","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AGI is defined as a marketing term coined in 1997 and later seized upon by companies like OpenAI as 'shorthand for a form of machine intelligence intended to rival and eventually surpass human intelligence' and 'central to their marketing efforts.'","citation":"Interest in AGI was revived in the 2010s when companies like OpenAI seized on the term, first as shorthand for a form of machine intelligence intended to rival and eventually surpass human intelligence, and later as a term \"central to their marketing efforts.\"","source_id":"src-42ed4cbf29ff","date":"2025-06-02","confidence":"high","x":0.28376376041030005,"y":8.800673513860012,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Ill-defined","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":181,"name":"Safe Superintelligence Inc.","entity_type":"organization","category":"Frontier Lab","definition":"Superintelligence is defined as a computer-based agent capable of surpassing human intelligence.","citation":"The company's mission is to focus on safely developing a superintelligence, a computer-based agent capable of surpassing human intelligence.","source_id":"src-88c03c9b0d86","date":"2024-06-18","confidence":"high","x":0.38571910681519783,"y":4.481333951507277,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":183,"name":"Forethought (AI Safety Research Nonprofit)","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"An AI system, or collection of systems, that is capable of doing essentially all economically useful tasks that human beings can do and doing so more cheaply than the relevant humans at any level of expertise.","citation":"By \"AGI\" I mean an AI system, or collection of systems, that is capable of doing essentially all economically useful tasks that human beings can do and doing so more cheaply than the relevant humans at any level of expertise. (This is a much higher bar than some people mean when they say \"AGI\".)","source_id":"src-ebf5bbed6851","date":"2026-01-27","confidence":"high","x":-0.08148486945846757,"y":2.1098833542579922,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":184,"name":"Narrow Path (by ControlAI)","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"ControlAI focuses on artificial superintelligence - AI vastly smarter than humans that surpasses collective human capabilities","citation":"Companies across the globe are investing to create artificial superintelligence – that they believe will surpass the collective capabilities of all humans. It is purely a question of whether such an intelligence exists, either as a single monolithic AI model or a collection of AI systems combined together to achieve an intellect that is more capable than humans in practically every field.","source_id":"src-43349ebf7a09","date":"2024-10-01","confidence":"high","x":0.5066550684555817,"y":4.641973440444098,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":187,"name":"AI Safety Camp","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AGI systems that act (semi-)autonomously in a variety of environments, interacting with humans","citation":"We will explore a neglected and novel design for generic AGI agents – AGI systems that act (semi-)autonomously in a variety of environments, interacting with humans – and their implementation in software.","source_id":"src-a4c137296efa","date":"2025-11-02","confidence":"high","x":-0.20918235266035043,"y":6.326263977635618,"stance":"Mixed/unclear","stance_score":null,"timeline":null,"timeline_score":null,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":191,"name":"Institute for AI Policy and Strategy (IAPS)","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AGI and superintelligence as advanced AI systems beyond today's most capable models, representing a spectrum of increasingly powerful AI whose implications IAPS works to govern.","citation":"The Institute for AI Policy and Strategy (IAPS) is a nonpartisan think tank that produces policy research to address the implications of AI, from today's most advanced models to potential AGI and superintelligence.","source_id":"src-df4ed62b127f","date":"2026-01-12","confidence":"medium","x":0.6122889143316865,"y":5.671312307513463,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":192,"name":"Foresight Institute","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"the possible future one‐to‐one modeling of the function of the human brain","citation":"While Artificial Intelligence has progressed dramatically over the last decade, 2024 may be remembered as the year that 'AGI' became a feature, not a bug, of corporate R&D efforts. Calls for safety and concern have taken a backseat to competitive pursuit. Interest in creating aligned AGI may not be sufficient without a clearer strategy for how alignment might be achieved.","source_id":"src-a6871e5c6dce","date":"2024-09-17","confidence":"medium","x":1.0794376510772883,"y":2.8972298552487303,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":204,"name":"Meta AI","entity_type":"organization","category":"Frontier Lab","definition":"AGI involves breadth of intelligence capabilities including reasoning and intuition, rather than a specific threshold, with arrival being a gradual process.","citation":"I don't have a one-sentence, pithy definition. You can quibble about if general intelligence is akin to human level intelligence, or is it like human-plus, or is it some far-future super intelligence. But to me, the important part is actually the breadth of it, which is that intelligence has all these different capabilities where you have to be able to reason and have intuition.","source_id":"src-abda651548f1","date":"2024-01-18","confidence":"high","x":-0.9759091383801876,"y":8.56205108379534,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":205,"name":"Center for AI Standards and Innovation (CAISI)","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"AI agents are defined as systems capable of autonomous actions that can work autonomously for hours, write and debug code, manage emails and calendars, and shop for goods","citation":"The Initiative will ensure that the next generation of AI—AI agents capable of autonomous actions—is widely adopted with confidence, can function securely on behalf of its users, and can interoperate smoothly across the digital ecosystem.","source_id":"src-b21e0019979c","date":"2026-02-17","confidence":"high","x":-0.6327376612885957,"y":5.076512936043791,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":206,"name":"AE Studio","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"Human-level general intelligence achieved through reinforcement learning paradigm with capabilities across diverse tasks and ability to learn from experience","citation":"AE Studio is proud to announce an amazing Reinforcement Learning paradigm that is guaranteed to achieve the performance of a human-level AGI. The technology yields an emergent intelligence via a unique combination of neural networks and genetic algorithms. The resulting intelligence is both generalized, and able to adapt and improve over time.","source_id":"src-3d15c7f1bd55","date":"2023-01-31","confidence":"high","x":1.834778328817484,"y":3.6430690232313534,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":210,"name":"SAG-AFTRA","entity_type":"organization","category":"Labor/Civil Society","definition":"SAG-AFTRA defines generative artificial intelligence as a subset of artificial intelligence that learns patterns from data and produces content based on those patterns, distinguishing it from traditional AI technologies programmed for specific functions.","citation":"\"Generative Artificial Intelligence\" is defined as: a subset of artificial intelligence that learns patterns from data and produces content based on those patterns (e.g., ChatGPT4, MidJourney, Dall-E2). It does not include 'traditional AI' technologies programmed to perform specific functions (e.g., CGI and VFX), such as those already used during all stages of motion picture production.","source_id":"src-4439d5895fc9","date":"2023-11-17","confidence":"high","x":1.1837433224100384,"y":6.381163631080228,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":211,"name":"Andreessen Horowitz (a16z)","entity_type":"organization","category":"VC/Capital/Philanthropy","definition":"AGI is defined as a computer system that is able to autonomously perform the majority of intellectual work.","citation":"In our OpenAI charter. We define it as a computer system that is able to autonomously perform the majority of intellectual work.","source_id":"src-0de779f78552","date":"2023-09-24","confidence":"high","x":0.09985898837983627,"y":8.63538814321123,"stance":"Accelerate","stance_score":1,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Overstated","risk_score":1,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":212,"name":"AI Futures Project","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AGI roughly means AI that can do almost everything, though they abandon the term and define more precise concepts like Automated Coder (AC), SIAR, TED-AI instead","citation":"AGI stands for Artificial General Intelligence, which roughly speaking means AI that can do almost everything. Different people give different definitions for it; in our work we basically abandon the term and define more precise concepts instead, such as AC, SIAR, TED-AI, etc.","source_id":"src-35fa0e9c8054","date":"2025-12-31","confidence":"high","x":0.8004590079292448,"y":7.782814194351986,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":213,"name":"Mistral AI","entity_type":"organization","category":"Frontier Lab","definition":"AGI is \"too simple of a concept\" - \"There's no such thing as one system that is going to be solving all of the problems of the world... It's never going to exist.\" Enterprises need specialized systems, not a single AGI abstraction.","citation":"There's no such thing as one system that is going to be solving all of the problems of the world... It's never going to exist. Just like you don't have any human that is able to solve every task in the world, you of course have to have some level of specialization to actually solve problems.","source_id":"src-e497be582a7a","date":"2026-01-28","confidence":"high","x":-0.7692992138900334,"y":8.98607244751445,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":215,"name":"Compassion in Machine Learning (CaML)","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"CaML refers to AGI in the context of increasingly autonomous AI systems that make decisions and take actions on behalf of humans at scale, with particular concern about alignment and default values in such systems.","citation":"AI agents are increasingly booking travel, managing schedules, and making purchasing decisions. As these systems scale, their default values get enacted millions of times. A travel agent that books a dolphin captivity show because it's the best keyword match isn't malicious, it's just indifferent. But indifference at scale is the problem. Models should take into account the impacts on non-humans just like they consider the impacts on humans. As AIs become increasingly autonomous and powerful, agentic benchmarks become increasingly important.","source_id":"src-9128236ebc1c","date":"2026-03-30","confidence":"medium","x":-0.10228884983493484,"y":7.186438583067193,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":217,"name":"Apollo Research","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"Apollo defines scheming as covertly pursuing unintended and misaligned goals, where a sufficiently capable scheming AI passes evaluations and appears aligned while pursuing outcomes its developers would not endorse.","citation":"We define scheming as covertly pursuing unintended and misaligned goals. A sufficiently capable scheming AI passes evaluations, follows instructions when monitored, and appears aligned, all while pursuing outcomes its developers would not endorse.","source_id":"src-7e9bdcc03677","date":"2026-01-19","confidence":"high","x":-0.641970773950535,"y":6.812931938832784,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":218,"name":"Alignment Research Center (ARC)","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"ARC focuses on 'intent alignment' - designing AI systems that are trying to do what their operators want, with particular concern about systems that could manipulate and deceive humans.","citation":"ML systems can exhibit goal-directed behavior, but it is difficult to understand or control what they are 'trying' to do. Powerful models could cause harm if they were trying to manipulate and deceive humans. The goal of intent alignment is to instead train these models to be helpful and honest.","source_id":"src-8d437ae058f8","date":"2023-03-03","confidence":"high","x":-0.16069111702693425,"y":4.032949324820118,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":219,"name":"Center for Human-Compatible AI (CHAI)","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"Machines that match or exceed human capabilities in every relevant dimension, capable of doing autonomously everything that humans can do but at much lower cost and greater scale","citation":"In fact, from its earliest days, the stated goal has been general-purpose artificial intelligence, sometimes called AGI or artificial general intelligence: machines that match or exceed human capabilities in every relevant dimension. By definition, general-purpose AI can do autonomously everything that humans can do, but at much lower cost and much greater scale.","source_id":"src-632b1c2c806f","date":"2023-09-10","confidence":"high","x":0.16083319669071428,"y":1.9423928380260953,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":220,"name":"Conjecture","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AGI is an AI that can match or exceed the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult","citation":"AGI is an AI that can match or exceed the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult.","source_id":"src-6233799b8c55","date":"2025-12-03","confidence":"high","x":1.1734554171859841,"y":9.281264467982368,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":221,"name":"BlueDot Impact","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AGI is defined as a highly autonomous system that outperforms humans at most economically valuable work, or alternatively as an AI which can perform at least 95% of economically-relevant tasks at human-level or above.","citation":"Artificial General Intelligence (AGI), which OpenAI describes as \"a highly autonomous system that outperforms humans at most economically valuable work\" has been the ultimate ambition of AI researchers for many decades.","source_id":"src-8e03917a7b5b","date":"2025-06-02","confidence":"high","x":-1.2571136135637064,"y":7.330334301744324,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":222,"name":"Secure AI Project","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AGI is implicitly treated as a near-term advanced AI capability threshold representing a transformative and unprecedented technological revolution requiring immediate policy preparation.","citation":"With artificial general intelligence (AGI) on the horizon, we must be prepared. The Alliance for Secure AI is working to educate the public about what needs to be done to prepare for this unprecedented technological revolution.","source_id":"src-1457b065682a","date":"2025-04-26","confidence":"low","x":-1.4993506623915684,"y":8.185151846379272,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":223,"name":"New Consensus","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AGI as a system that would be converted into a public research utility upon corporate failure, distinct from current AI systems based on speculative valuations.","citation":"No Payoff for Hype: Investors who bought in at 100x revenue multiples based on future 'AGI' promises will be wiped out. The government pays only for the 'bricks and mortar' of the digital age—physical infrastructure and proven intellectual property—ensuring the public gets a fair deal on the assets it is acquiring.","source_id":"src-4becff0f8eeb","date":"2025-12-10","confidence":"low","x":-0.24434130454784742,"y":9.521202904973043,"stance":"Nationalize","stance_score":7,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":224,"name":"Center for a New American Security (CNAS)","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AI system capable of performing a wide range of cognitive tasks at or above human expert levels","citation":"Artificial general intelligence typically refers to an AI system capable of performing a wide range of cognitive tasks at or above human expert levels.","source_id":"src-a6ea82a77479","date":"2025-12-04","confidence":"high","x":1.621574333191922,"y":3.144724660935002,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":225,"name":"Centre for the Governance of AI (GovAI)","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"GovAI focuses on general-purpose AI systems, which they distinguish from narrow AI, emphasizing systems with broad capabilities across multiple domains rather than a specific threshold of performance.","citation":"Our largest focus has been on general-purpose AI systems and their implications for security. Researchers at GovAI seek to understand how general-purpose AI may both contribute to and mitigate risks in domains such as cybersecurity, biosecurity, and economic security.","source_id":"src-4066e6cd91d5","date":"2025-11-04","confidence":"high","x":1.3831612117006333,"y":5.670555440738867,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":226,"name":"AI Policy Institute","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"Human-level AI systems capable of general intelligence across cognitive domains","citation":"believe human-level AI (AGI) will be developed within 5 years.","source_id":"src-c07492675966","date":"2023-08-03","confidence":"medium","x":1.7712295851728264,"y":3.5949122813726873,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":228,"name":"Americans for Responsible Innovation (ARI)","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AGI represents AI systems that match or exceed human intelligence across practically all cognitive domains with flexibility to solve unfamiliar problems, transfer knowledge between domains, understand context, form novel goals, and potentially improve its own capabilities.","citation":"Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) represents a watershed technological development in human history—AI systems that match or exceed human intelligence across practically all cognitive domains. Unlike today's specialized AI that excels in narrow tasks, AGI would possess the flexibility to solve unfamiliar problems, transfer knowledge between domains, understand context, form novel goals, and potentially improve its own capabilities.","source_id":"src-649eba135a43","date":"2025-04-14","confidence":"high","x":1.0271961716861038,"y":7.370918677121788,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":229,"name":"Future of Life Institute","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) is a system about as capable as a human across a wide range of domains, while superintelligence is a system that far surpasses human cognitive abilities.","citation":"The product of an intelligence explosion would be not just Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) – a system about as capable as a human across a wide range of domains – but a superintelligence, a system that far surpasses our cognitive abilities.","source_id":"src-e49b6ceff6df","date":"2025-03-21","confidence":"high","x":0.6823422340476305,"y":6.267436938310296,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":232,"name":"Senate Commerce Committee (AI jurisdiction)","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"The AI Working Group recognizes that there is not widespread agreement on the definition of AGI or threshold by which it will officially be achieved.","citation":"At the same time, the AI Working Group recognizes that there is not widespread agreement on the definition of AGI or threshold by which it will officially be achieved.","source_id":"src-c1e776c5f0d6","date":"2024-05-14","confidence":"high","x":-1.861528796834176,"y":8.912605277059246,"stance":"Mixed/unclear","stance_score":null,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":234,"name":"European AI Office","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"AGI is a stage of AI development where AI would be capable to perform a wide range of cognitive tasks with similar or better results than humans","citation":"Artificial general intelligence (AGI) is a broad concept referring to a stage of development of AI where AI would be capable to perform a wide range of cognitive tasks with similar or better results than humans.","source_id":"src-984fe0c657d0","date":"2024-07-24","confidence":"high","x":0.8580036725637642,"y":8.275753831136932,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":235,"name":"MIT Algorithmic Alignment Group","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI describes the potential of artificial intelligence to match or surpass human cognitive capabilities","citation":"\"Ensuring AI isn't misused or acts contrary to our intentions is increasingly important as we approach artificial general intelligence (AGI),\" says Lorvo, a computer science, economics, and data science major. AGI describes the potential of artificial intelligence to match or surpass human cognitive capabilities.","source_id":"src-6fa293e77551","date":"2025-02-04","confidence":"low","x":1.340389817619337,"y":7.867718292833814,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":236,"name":"Future of Humanity Institute (closed 2024)","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"Superintelligent AI / AGI is an AI system whose creation is likely to be humanity's 'final act — for good or ill,' capable of replacing or surpassing human intelligence across all domains.","citation":"The resulting book, the bestselling Superintelligence, warned humanity that the creation of superintelligent AI is likely to be our final act — for good or ill.","source_id":"src-dd03465add8b","date":"2014-01-01","confidence":"high","x":0.20978193107094337,"y":6.5207062749111335,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":238,"name":"Tsinghua University (Institute for AI International Governance & Center for AI Governance)","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is defined through five progressive levels of trustworthiness — perception, reasoning, decision-making, autonomy, and collaboration — framed as a system that reliably avoids harmful behaviors and operates with high autonomy in safety-critical domains.","citation":"Building upon this framework, we define five levels of trustworthy AGI: perception, reasoning, decision-making, autonomy, and collaboration trustworthiness. These levels represent distinct yet progressive aspects of trustworthy AGI.","source_id":"src-11a485ad0a51","date":"2024-12-01","confidence":"medium","x":-0.273835131627489,"y":7.744594158739927,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":242,"name":"EA Long-Term Future Fund","entity_type":"organization","category":"VC/Capital/Philanthropy","definition":"An AI system (or collection of systems) that can fully automate the vast majority (>90%) of roles in the 2025 economy, where a job is fully automatable when machines could be built to carry out the job better and more cheaply than human workers.","citation":"We defined AGI as: An AI system (or collection of systems) that can fully automate the vast majority (>90%) of roles in the 2025 economy. A job is fully automatable when machines could be built to carry out the job better and more cheaply than human workers. Think feasibility, not adoption.","source_id":"src-93e031e049a8","date":"2026-02-01","confidence":"high","x":-0.020617064292638643,"y":2.0642904308946455,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":246,"name":"ControlAI","entity_type":"organization","category":"Labor/Civil Society","definition":"ControlAI defines artificial superintelligence as AI vastly smarter than humans that would be capable of replacing humans both individually and collectively as a species.","citation":"At ControlAI, our mission is to prevent the risk of extinction posed by artificial superintelligence – AI vastly smarter than humans. This would be AI capable of replacing humans, both individually and collectively as a species.","source_id":"src-e5d648989aaa","date":"2026-04-01","confidence":"high","x":0.4398938426144056,"y":4.6424381202228195,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":247,"name":"MIT FutureTech","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"Artificial Super Intelligence – a level of machine intelligence that surpasses the current state of the art in AI, going beyond statistics, processing and pattern toward deep reasoning, and autonomous solving across disciplines.","citation":"The broad goal of U.S. AI policy should be to drive toward what we call Artificial Super Intelligence – a level of machine intelligence that surpasses the current state of the art in AI, going beyond statistics, processing and pattern toward deep reasoning, and autonomous solving across disciplines.","source_id":"src-c7b938501028","date":"2025-04-09","confidence":"high","x":0.576721358764378,"y":4.339472682895066,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":254,"name":"Stop AI","entity_type":"organization","category":"Labor/Civil Society","definition":"Systems that are more capable than all human experts across all technical domains","citation":"Our main demand is that we're trying to permanently ban the development of artificial general intelligence, or AGI. And roughly speaking, that's systems that are more capable than all human experts across all technical domains.","source_id":"src-29403ed6a72d","date":"2025-02-19","confidence":"high","x":1.0639980918231533,"y":3.207178462042388,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":256,"name":"Buddhism & AI Initiative","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AGI is conceived as a powerful AI that can match or exceed human capabilities on any task, contrasted with narrow AI systems good at just one thing.","citation":"Artificial General Intelligence('AGI') is conceived as a powerful AI that can match or exceed human capabilities on any task.","source_id":"src-b154ac053cd4","date":"2026-02-17","confidence":"high","x":0.8562728020935994,"y":7.212837025306832,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":null,"timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":257,"name":"Astera Neuro & AGI","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"Human-like Artificial General Intelligence based on neuroscience-informed foundational principles","citation":"Our AI effort is pursuing an exploratory, neuroscience-informed approach to developing the foundational principles of human-like Artificial General Intelligence.","source_id":"src-5ebab9764a5b","date":"2026-02-13","confidence":"high","x":1.6829155549033539,"y":3.6786922778720985,"stance":"Mixed/unclear","stance_score":null,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":270,"name":"PauseAI","entity_type":"organization","category":"Labor/Civil Society","definition":"General artificial intelligence systems that are more powerful than current models and have dangerous capabilities","citation":"PauseAI is a global political movement founded in the Netherlands with the stated aim of achieving global coordination to stop the development of more powerful general artificial intelligence systems, at least until it is known how to build them safely, and keep them under democratic control.","source_id":"src-24b15e21e679","date":"2023-04-30","confidence":"high","x":1.4535368114117058,"y":4.6838716831976805,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":272,"name":"Palisade Research","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AI systems that could pose a strategic threat to humans, including systems capable of self-improvement with minimal human input and fully autonomous AI researchers","citation":"The world is largely unprepared for AI systems that could pose a strategic threat to humans. Right now, the government has limited capacity to evaluate loss-of-control risks, and almost no ability to impose limits on AI systems that could pose these risks—like systems capable of self-improvement with minimal human input. Meanwhile, AI companies are actively working to build fully autonomous AI researchers.","source_id":"src-3a391e5120d2","date":"2025-12-18","confidence":"high","x":-0.3238490290211218,"y":3.0969227812778524,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"autonomous-research-capability","cluster_label":"Autonomous Research"},{"entity_id":274,"name":"Center for Long-Term Cybersecurity","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"AI systems that can autonomously pursue goals and take actions with little to no human oversight, often through interaction with external environments and tools.","citation":"A new paper authored by researchers from the Center for Long-Term Cybersecurity's Artificial Intelligence Security Initiative (AISI) focuses on \"AI agents\" or \"agentic AI,\" AI systems that can autonomously pursue goals and take actions with little to no human oversight, often through interaction with external environments and tools.","source_id":"src-01aa20b317c3","date":"2026-02-01","confidence":"high","x":-0.7089537235238121,"y":4.85936082580385,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":284,"name":"Long-Term Future Fund","entity_type":"organization","category":"VC/Capital/Philanthropy","definition":"AGI is treated as a transformative and potentially catastrophic advanced artificial intelligence system posing global catastrophic and existential risks, with 'advanced AI' used interchangeably; not formally defined but operationalized through the lens of x-risk.","citation":"The Long-Term Future Fund aims to positively influence the long-term trajectory of civilization by making grants that address global catastrophic risks, especially potential risks from advanced artificial intelligence and pandemics.","source_id":"src-74f5f4d5b997","date":"2023-08-09","confidence":"medium","x":-1.7780403953365926,"y":8.080469221549693,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":293,"name":"Centre for Future Generations","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AI systems matching or exceeding humans at most economically useful cognitive work","citation":"We adopt the working definition of 'AI systems matching or exceeding humans at most economically useful cognitive work'.","source_id":"src-afd3f9b5831e","date":"2025-12-16","confidence":"high","x":1.335733746922248,"y":2.2361569837699697,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":294,"name":"Good Ancestors","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AI models with human-like cognitive capabilities","citation":"Markets forecast that Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) – AI models with human-like cognitive capabilities – will be developed during this term of government.","source_id":"src-2f058a1cf455","date":"2025-05-13","confidence":"high","x":1.498230454063996,"y":2.7496249898889507,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":296,"name":"The AI Policy Network","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AI systems that match or exceed human intelligence across practically all cognitive domains, with flexibility to solve unfamiliar problems and transfer knowledge between domains.","citation":"Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) represents a watershed technological development in human history—AI systems that match or exceed human intelligence across practically all cognitive domains. Unlike today's specialized AI that excels in narrow tasks, AGI would possess the flexibility to solve unfamiliar problems, transfer knowledge between domains, understand context, form novel goals, and potentially improve its own capabilities.","source_id":"src-649eba135a43","date":"2025-03-15","confidence":"high","x":1.1930278240226433,"y":3.4470969971331806,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":297,"name":"Global AI Moratorium (GAIM)","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"Defines focus as artificial superintelligence (ASI) systems rather than AGI specifically - systems that could surpass human intelligence and control","citation":"Harry and Meghan join over two dozen prominent signatories supporting a statement organized by the Future of Life Institute that demands \"a prohibition on the development of superintelligence\" until specific safety conditions are met.","source_id":"src-beeaeb571540","date":"2025-10-21","confidence":"high","x":0.6726518175479618,"y":4.994731650540343,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":301,"name":"The Alliance for Secure AI Action","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"Systems that can reason, strategize, and override human decision-making; machines that can outthink, outmaneuver, and outlast humans","citation":"Artificial General Intelligence—AGI—isn't a futuristic fantasy. It's the explicit goal of today's most powerful AI companies. Systems that can reason, strategize, and override human decision-making are already being deployed.","source_id":"src-be8b86c38bc8","date":"2025-06-12","confidence":"high","x":0.948080567789264,"y":3.175234406427937,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":302,"name":"Lightcone Infrastructure","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AGI characterized as 'machine gods beyond our comprehension and control'","citation":"AGI sure looks to me like it's coming, and it's coming uncomfortably fast. While I expect the overall choice to build machine gods beyond our comprehension and control will be quite bad for the world, the hope that remains routes in substantial chunks through leveraging the nascent AGI systems that we have access to today and will see in the coming years.","source_id":"src-056d8f80dff4","date":"2024-11-29","confidence":"medium","x":0.5964399659910222,"y":8.488167087884344,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":304,"name":"The Midas Project","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"Human-level intelligence that can produce or surpass human cognitive capabilities","citation":"The first is that AI progress appears on track to produce, or surpass, human-level intelligence this decade. The second is that AI developers are consistently failing to manage risks and prioritize social welfare.","source_id":"src-9b583cf5915d","date":"2024-12-14","confidence":"medium","x":1.7848696870586656,"y":3.2322026997267974,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":308,"name":"Global Catastrophic Risk Institute","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"Systems with some generality, being able to field inquiries across a wide range of domains","citation":"Current state-of-the-art systems already have some generality, being able to field inquiries across a wide range of domains, even while they still have significant limitations.","source_id":"src-4a29d78b85e8","date":"2025-04-28","confidence":"high","x":1.3329045573599831,"y":3.851454620085487,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":309,"name":"Global Partnership on AI","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"AGI typically refers to AI systems that can perform a wide range of intellectual tasks at or above human level, with capabilities that generalize across domains, distinguished from current AI systems which excel in narrow domains but lack broader capabilities.","citation":"While definitions vary, Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) typically refers to AI systems that can perform a wide range of intellectual tasks at or above human level, with capabilities that generalize across domains.","source_id":"src-afbef8059dd3","date":"2025-03-01","confidence":"high","x":0.7053268183525715,"y":6.933748184669553,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":314,"name":"Odyssean Institute","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AGI is referenced in the context of requiring democratic processes for oversight, but no explicit definition is provided beyond it being a powerful technology requiring governance.","citation":"In 2023, OpenAI launched the \"Democratic Inputs to AI\" program, funding 10 global teams to test new ways of surfacing public preferences about AI behavior, developing a \"democratic processes for overseeing AGI.\"","source_id":"src-d3da313736ac","date":"2025-09-28","confidence":"medium","x":-0.36566340080863396,"y":9.297015351841617,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":315,"name":"AI Safety Initiative at Georgia Tech","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"General purpose AI systems as a universal problem solver that leading AI labs are creating.","citation":"Many experts believe there is a panacea on the horizon: general purpose AI systems. Leading AI labs have set their sights on creating a universal problem solver, pouring significant resources into accelerating AI development.","source_id":"src-609029832056","date":"2023-05-29","confidence":"high","x":1.535100355387437,"y":4.533018556655391,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":317,"name":"Probably Good","entity_type":"organization","category":"Labor/Civil Society","definition":"AI that can reason and plan in all ways humans can, representing human-level or superhuman-level intelligence","citation":"Current artificial intelligence still can't reason and plan in all ways humans can. Because of this, anticipating the consequences of future AI systems is bound to be more speculative than thinking about the problems we face today. The timelines for human-level AI or AI that is more meaningfully autonomous remain a matter of much debate.","source_id":"src-9fe71c782b89","date":"2024-11-19","confidence":"medium","x":0.5482962293840608,"y":3.3907096596929365,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":322,"name":"Global Challenges Project","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI was defined as a general-purpose AI that can learn, edit its code, and act autonomously to address novel problems with novel and complex strategies similar to or better than humans","citation":"For this study, AGI was defined as a general-purpose AI that can learn, edit its code, and act autonomously to address novel problems with novel and complex strategies similar to or better than humans, as distinct from Artificial Narrow Intelligence (ANI) that has a narrower purpose.","source_id":"src-9ed71714581a","date":"2024-04-14","confidence":"high","x":0.6662624118307175,"y":7.477986626536701,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"autonomous-research-capability","cluster_label":"Autonomous Research"},{"entity_id":325,"name":"London AI Safety Research Labs (LASR Labs)","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"LASR Labs refers to superintelligent AI as systems that surpass human intelligence, requiring control mechanisms and ethical guidelines.","citation":"Looking further into the future, LASR Labs tackles questions about superintelligent AI—systems that surpass human intelligence. They focus on ensuring that if and when such systems are developed, they act in humanity's best interest.","source_id":"src-c38c687eceae","date":"2024-11-27","confidence":"medium","x":0.507141066465925,"y":4.6610915595931575,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":326,"name":"Roman Yampolskiy","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is a system capable of performing in any domain a human could perform, creating an average artificial person that can do cognitive labor and physical labor.","citation":"So the definitions we used to have, and people are modifying them a little bit lately, artificial general intelligence was a system capable of performing in any domain a human could perform. So you're creating this average artificial person. They can do cognitive labor, physical labor where you can get another human to do it.","source_id":"src-88e25477aac7","date":"2024-06-02","confidence":"high","x":0.36462292727438333,"y":7.96714384004806,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":327,"name":"Dylan Hadfield-Menell","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is implicitly treated as a system capable of recursive self-improvement and transformative societal change, but Hadfield-Menell is skeptical of a single 'intelligence explosion' within one digital entity, viewing recursive improvement as occurring in aggregate across organizations rather than within a single AI system.","citation":"While I would not rule it out, I tend to think that the idea of an 'intelligence explosion', is a good deal more questionable than I.J. Good does. This is because I think that 'intelligence' is a complicated property with multiple competing dimensions and I've learned from experience to be wary of intuition in these settings.","source_id":"src-7135fa126f09","date":"2024-01-18","confidence":"medium","x":-0.15140930137997105,"y":8.467502915168465,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":328,"name":"Steve Byrnes's Brain-Like AGI Safety","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AGI as systems using brain-like algorithms that can autonomously invent science and engineering from scratch, found and run companies, understand the world, build and share knowledge, collaborate, figure things out, get things done, invent new tools and technologies to solve their problems.","citation":"It's this scenario that says: maybe future researchers will reverse engineer, or perhaps reinvent, algorithms that are similar to those that power the human brain. So again, humans can do all those things mentioned in the previous slides—invent science and engineering from scratch, found and run companies, and so on—so there's something in the human brain that allows them to do all those things. And an AGI could do the same thing via the same kinds of algorithms.","source_id":"src-55c67bde8dce","date":"2025-05-07","confidence":"high","x":0.03299500129816073,"y":9.018402017410644,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"autonomous-research-capability","cluster_label":"Autonomous Research"},{"entity_id":331,"name":"Formation Research","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"Generally intelligent AI system (AGI) that could competently pursue some goal and prevent interference from humans due to instrumentally convergent goal preservation.","citation":"It is possible that lock-in can be led by an autonomous AI system or group of AI systems. For example, a generally intelligent AI system (AGI) could competently pursue some goal and prevent interference from humans due to the instrumentally convergent goal of goal preservation, resulting in a situation where the AGI pursues that goal for a long time.","source_id":"src-2fe52fa2c063","date":"2025-03-04","confidence":"medium","x":-0.1790706839538042,"y":7.740690977739367,"stance":"Mixed/unclear","stance_score":null,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":341,"name":"Machine Intelligence Research Institute (MIRI)","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AI that substantially surpasses humans in all capacities, including economic, scientific, and military ones","citation":"The stated goal of the world's leading AI companies is to build AI that is general enough to do anything a human can do, from solving hard problems in theoretical physics to deftly navigating social environments. Recent machine learning progress seems to have brought this goal within reach. At this point, we would be uncomfortable ruling out the possibility that AI more capable than any human is achieved in the next year or two, and we would be moderately surprised if this outcome were still two decades away.","source_id":"src-a11a0e651119","date":"2024-12-19","confidence":"high","x":0.1725362994790436,"y":2.1850315526224016,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":344,"name":"Public AI Network","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"Public AI should be built by the public sector ensuring AI capacity is not limited to big technical platforms, accessible ensuring AI benefits society, and accountable ensuring it reflects society's values","citation":"Public AI should be built by the public sector: ensuring AI capacity is not limited to bit technical platforms. It should be accessible, ensuring AI benefits society. And it should be accountable, ensuring it reflects its society's values.","source_id":"src-fecdd26c7a53","date":"2023-11-08","confidence":"high","x":-0.5439373477325881,"y":3.615142432421111,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"augmentative-tools","cluster_label":"Augmentative Tools"},{"entity_id":351,"name":"80,000 Hours","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AI systems that match human performance at most knowledge work, or at least human level or better at most cognitive tasks","citation":"Typically, when people say 'AGI' what they have in mind is something like 'at least human level or better at most cognitive tasks.' This is roughly what I'll take it to mean in this article.","source_id":"src-74152c598e9b","date":"2025-03-21","confidence":"high","x":1.0976663776087812,"y":2.7760813266206688,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":352,"name":"Heron AI Security Initiative","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"Transformative AI — AI systems capable of reshaping global power dynamics and automating significant portions of skilled labor — used interchangeably with references to 'rogue AI' that could autonomously seize compute resources and act against human interests.","citation":"What does Security for Transformative AI mean? Even ignoring the recent use of 'AI Security' in place of 'AI Safety' in the policy world, security covers a huge surface area of work. I'm using the classical definition of 'protecting information systems against unauthorized use.'","source_id":"src-d2eee7b7f372","date":"2026-01-04","confidence":"medium","x":-2.060730501750596,"y":7.7970832955822535,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":358,"name":"Saving Humanity from Homo Sapiens (SHfHS)","entity_type":"organization","category":"VC/Capital/Philanthropy","definition":"Full AGI is synonymous with 'super-human general-purpose AI' — an AI system able to perform essentially all human cognitive tasks at or above top human expert level, acquire new skills, and transfer capability to new domains autonomously, with no needed help or oversight.","citation":"We'll define 'full' AGI to be synonymous with 'super-human general-purpose AI' meaning an AI system that is able to perform essentially all human cognitive tasks at or above top human expert level, as well as acquire new skills and transfer capability to new domains. This is in keeping with how 'AGI' is often defined in the modern literature.","source_id":"src-06f8ed43b9e8","date":"2025-03-05","confidence":"high","x":0.2609514992494838,"y":7.0142895949050565,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":362,"name":"The AI Whistleblower Initiative (AIWI)","entity_type":"organization","category":"Labor/Civil Society","definition":"AGI is understood as advanced AI developed primarily by private frontier labs rather than governments, potentially transformative enough to warrant dedicated insider oversight mechanisms; referenced in the context of supporting 'insiders at the frontier of AI' and the possibility that AGI could join a short list of truly revolutionary technologies not heavily shaped by government.","citation":"Another factor which exacerbates the gravity of the situation is that, barring nationalisation, Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) might add to a short list of truly revolutionary technologies whose development was not conducted, funded or at least heavily shaped by a government agency (cf. nuclear weapons, space technologies, radar, GPS, microprocessors).","source_id":"src-889a63691b75","date":"2025-08-01","confidence":"medium","x":0.10245359960939045,"y":9.353728232743855,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":365,"name":"Center for AI Risk Management & Alignment (CARMA)","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"CARMA uses the term 'transformative AI' rather than AGI, referring to AI systems that pose existential risks to humanity and the biosphere","citation":"CARMA's mission is to markedly mitigate the risks to humanity and to the biosphere from unaligned transformative artificial intelligence, via tightly-integrated technical, strategy, and policy research competencies.","source_id":"src-b264766b6d03","date":"2024-01-01","confidence":"high","x":-1.9594376240083686,"y":7.945927510529962,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":372,"name":"Global Priorities Institute (University of Oxford)","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"AI systems that are generally smarter than humans","citation":"Such models still face severe limits and fall short of Artificial General Intelligence. Humans still conduct the most important scientific research and write the most acclaimed novels. These models remain largely inscrutable, even to the people who design and operate them.","source_id":"src-abcdf69463f6","date":"2024-07-04","confidence":"medium","x":0.310297266125656,"y":3.221171499888327,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":376,"name":"LawZero","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AGI is an AI that can match or exceed the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult, operationalized across ten core cognitive domains derived from Cattell-Horn-Carroll theory.","citation":"AGI is an AI that can match or exceed the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult... The resulting AGI scores (e.g., GPT-4 at 27%, GPT-5 at 57%) concretely quantify both rapid progress and the substantial gap remaining before AGI.","source_id":"src-6233799b8c55","date":"2025-10-20","confidence":"high","x":1.301606608315846,"y":9.273641367355033,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":380,"name":"Simplex","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AGI refers to advanced AI systems that are 'compatible with humanity' and toward which Simplex aims to guide development; implicitly understood as AI scaling to superhuman capabilities (ASI), with outcomes ranging from extinction to flourishing depending on alignment.","citation":"Our mission at Simplex is to develop a principled science of intelligence, to help make advanced AI systems compatible with humanity. We're optimistic these insights can help create more options and guide the development of AGI towards better outcomes for humanity.","source_id":"src-7218f850eaa7","date":"2025-08-05","confidence":"medium","x":-0.08170556296732011,"y":7.627993142513333,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":381,"name":"Metaculus","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AGI requires passing a hard Turing test, having general robotic capabilities, achieving 75% accuracy on MMLU benchmark tasks with 90% mean accuracy, and achieving 90% accuracy on APPS coding benchmark.","citation":"The AI system needs to be able to: Pass a really hard Turing test. Have general robotic capabilities (being able to assemble a 'circa-2021 Ferrari 312 T4 1:8 scale automobile model' or equivalent). Achieve 'at least 75% accuracy in every task and 90% mean accuracy across all tasks' on the MMLU benchmark, which measures expertise in a wide range of academic subjects. Achieve at least 90% accuracy with a single attempt for each question on the APPS benchmark, which measures coding skills.","source_id":"src-0baf583b6112","date":"2025-02-04","confidence":"high","x":0.6010104316662798,"y":8.424986679372841,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":387,"name":"Longview Philanthropy","entity_type":"organization","category":"VC/Capital/Philanthropy","definition":"AGI (or human-level AI) is defined as AI systems that can outperform humans in most or virtually all cognitive domains, able to autonomously accomplish virtually every task better and more cheaply than humans.","citation":"Extrapolating these trends into the future suggest that we may be a decade or two away from AI systems which can outperform humans in most cognitive domains... half of the respondents stated that we are more likely than not to develop machines that can autonomously accomplish virtually every task better and more cheaply than humans before 2060.","source_id":"src-ff74c68935a1","date":"2023-09-28","confidence":"high","x":-0.6662813356978544,"y":7.452574349729181,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":390,"name":"Simon Institute for Longterm Governance","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AI systems that perform well on a wide range of cognitive tasks, with more demanding definitions requiring learning, reasoning, physical manipulation, and economically valuable work capabilities","citation":"Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) refers to AI systems that perform well on a wide range of cognitive tasks. More demanding AGI definitions also require that these AI systems can learn and reason, that they can physically manipulate objects in the real world, and that they produce economically valuable work.","source_id":"src-2a2a2aba4158","date":"2025-06-09","confidence":"high","x":0.738087329816891,"y":2.9543552156122592,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":392,"name":"The Future Society","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AI red lines are defined as specific, non-negotiable prohibitions on certain AI behaviors or AI uses that are deemed too dangerous, high-risk, or unethical to permit.","citation":"For the purpose of this piece, we define red lines in AI governance as specific, non-negotiable prohibitions on certain AI behaviors or AI uses that are deemed too dangerous, high-risk, or unethical to permit.","source_id":"src-7d1f6143bdec","date":"2025-07-02","confidence":"high","x":-1.6598466748005096,"y":7.6612254895715965,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":401,"name":"Pause House","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AGI refers to human-level artificial general intelligence that can think with inhuman speed and accuracy, able to do work in hours that would take human scientists years","citation":"Human level artificial general intelligence (AGI) is coming in a few years because a small number powerful corporations like Microsoft and OpenAI and few wealthy individuals like Sam Altman and Mark Zuckerberg have decided that their ability to develop AGI gives them the right to do it.","source_id":"src-fe181908e868","date":"2024-03-31","confidence":"high","x":1.2136989394043345,"y":8.01489494296695,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":407,"name":"The Compendium","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AGI is defined as AI able to do all tasks a human can on a computer, at which point it becomes functionally AGI and able to conduct AI research.","citation":"At the point when AI is able to do all of the tasks a human can on a computer, it will functionally be AGI and able to conduct the same AI research that we can.","source_id":"src-889a9071c9dc","date":"2024-10-31","confidence":"high","x":-0.7473861944792233,"y":8.282083399979152,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"autonomous-research-capability","cluster_label":"Autonomous Research"},{"entity_id":408,"name":"Convergence Analysis","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"Human-level AI capabilities that will emerge within 5 years, followed by intelligence beyond human capabilities","citation":"The development of AI technology poses both great opportunities and perils for humanity. We're currently at a watershed moment in history - plausibly, human-level AI will be here within 5 years. Shortly after this, we'll be in a world powered by intelligence beyond human capabilities.","source_id":"src-97d32d25031b","date":"2025-04-13","confidence":"high","x":1.800357175251213,"y":3.1139898187378376,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":418,"name":"PIBBSS Fellowship (Principles of Intelligent Behavior in Biological and Social Systems)","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is implicitly treated as advanced AI that transforms civilization, with 'post-AGI' framing used to denote a world in which AI has sufficiently advanced to reshape economies, governance structures, and culture, potentially leading to irreversible loss of human agency.","citation":"This track focuses on understanding systemic existential risks from incremental AI development and developing solutions to preserve meaningful human agency in a world transformed by advanced AI. Core Research Themes are: Post-AGI Economics, Post-AGI Culture, Post-AGI Governance.","source_id":"src-023a4e2a7afc","date":"2025-10-08","confidence":"medium","x":-1.7923557898970788,"y":7.98237753729842,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":422,"name":"Campaign for AI Safety","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"Defines AGI as AI that can be trained to be far more intelligent than any human, with the potential to threaten human values, dignity and existence.","citation":"Many leading AI researchers believe generative AI can eventually be trained to be far more intelligent than any human and may threaten human values, dignity and existence. Passing of national laws criminalising the development of any form of Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) or Artificial Superintelligence (ASI).","source_id":"src-a490f2f8a927","date":"2023-07-04","confidence":"high","x":-0.921651263744702,"y":8.056222505446065,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":426,"name":"Stop AGI","entity_type":"organization","category":"Labor/Civil Society","definition":"AI systems far more powerful than humans, which they call AGI and superintelligence, capable of dismantling the entire planet for resources, rebuilding humans into digital minds, and colonizing space.","citation":"By AGI, they don't just mean AI that could perform all human tasks, automate science, and build nuclear weapons. Anthropic CEO Dario Amodei says AGI will give us 'complete control over our own biology and neuroscience [and] could make us whoever and whatever we want to be'.","source_id":"src-895a90e5db77","date":"2023-04-05","confidence":"high","x":-0.33058919604696035,"y":2.5595974017822227,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":428,"name":"Advanced Research + Invention Agency (ARIA)","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"General-purpose AI that can perform a wide variety of tasks within specific domains, explicitly distinguished from AGI which would equal or surpass human performance on all cognitive tasks.","citation":"Importantly, general-purpose AI is not to be confused with 'Artificial General Intelligence' (AGI), a term sometimes used to refer to a potential future AI system that equals or surpasses human performance on all or almost all cognitive tasks. General-purpose AI is a much weaker concept.","source_id":"src-2f8277b52b13","date":"2024-06-09","confidence":"high","x":1.2812157185206634,"y":6.066089274120746,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":429,"name":"Institute for Law & AI (LawAI)","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AI agents that can generally outperform humans in cognitive tasks and economically valuable activities","citation":"The prospect of artificial superintelligence—AI agents that can generally outperform humans in cognitive tasks and economically valuable activities—will transform the legal order as we know it.","source_id":"src-ec05d8ac5821","date":"2026-02-25","confidence":"high","x":1.4984468472256036,"y":2.250644294681656,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":432,"name":"International Association for Safe & Ethical AI (IASEAI)","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AGI is contrasted with 'Tool AI' — Tool AI augments human capabilities within constrained, controlled boundaries, while AGI refers to unchecked, autonomous, general-purpose AI systems whose pursuit is seen as dangerous and unnecessary.","citation":"A central debate at IASEAI25 involved distinguishing between Tool AI—systems designed to augment human capabilities—and the often-hyped pursuit of Artificial General Intelligence (AGI). Max Tegmark argued that we do not need AGI; instead, our focus should be on developing tool AI within strictly regulated boundaries.","source_id":"src-104c64bd45d2","date":"2025-02-07","confidence":"medium","x":0.7373951576132275,"y":7.052387201685483,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"augmentative-tools","cluster_label":"Augmentative Tools"},{"entity_id":437,"name":"AI Safety Asia (AISA)","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AISA works to mitigate catastrophic AI risks, which appears to be their focus rather than defining AGI specifically.","citation":"Our goal is to mitigate catastrophic AI risks, reduce suffering from AI harms, and foster human flourishing by identifying harmonising levers on transnational cooperation for safe and governed AI across the Asia continent.","source_id":"src-c0db29358fde","date":"2025-12-16","confidence":"medium","x":-1.342741922330657,"y":7.980089544823468,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":443,"name":"Center for AI Policy (CAIP)","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"AGI is commonly understood as an AI system that can match or outperform humans at an extremely wide range of tasks.","citation":"Definitional details vary, but AGI is commonly understood as an AI system that can match or outperform humans at an extremely wide range of tasks.","source_id":"src-0b1e1c4af748","date":"2023-10-17","confidence":"high","x":0.3847220125267978,"y":7.606747044866848,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":533,"name":"UK AI Security Institute","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"Artificial general intelligence (AGI) describes a machine-driven capability to achieve human-level or higher performance across most cognitive tasks.","citation":"The risks and opportunities posed by a given model derive from its capabilities and how it is used, not the breadth of tasks it can match human performance in. As such, a focus on the concept of AGI may not be productive.","source_id":"src-d75be1daae0d","date":"2023-11-03","confidence":"high","x":1.5958961425545117,"y":6.945437819028443,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":null,"timeline_score":null,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":727,"name":"Cloudflare","entity_type":"organization","category":"Infrastructure & Compute","definition":"Artificial general intelligence (AGI) is the term for a computer's ability to think original thoughts, reason, plan, and otherwise duplicate human cognitive abilities.","citation":"Artificial general intelligence (AGI) is the term for a computer's ability to think original thoughts, reason, plan, and otherwise duplicate human cognitive abilities. In simpler terms, an AGI program would be, essentially, 'human' or 'conscious' in its intelligence.","source_id":"src-16c1e84da3dc","date":"2025-01-01","confidence":"high","x":1.4013651430737322,"y":7.551037849947054,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":728,"name":"Nvidia","entity_type":"organization","category":"Infrastructure & Compute","definition":"An AI system capable of starting, growing, and running a technology company worth more than $1 billion, but not necessarily sustaining it long-term","citation":"I think it's now. I think we've achieved AGI.","source_id":"src-b9f640a2a4dc","date":"2026-03-23","confidence":"high","x":-0.008723345396763827,"y":2.780126701466333,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":729,"name":"Amazon","entity_type":"organization","category":"Deployers & Platforms","definition":"Artificial general intelligence (AGI) is a field of theoretical AI research that attempts to create software with human-like intelligence and the ability to self-teach, able to perform tasks that it is not necessarily trained or developed for.","citation":"Artificial general intelligence (AGI) is a field of theoretical AI research that attempts to create software with human-like intelligence and the ability to self-teach. The aim is for the software to be able to perform tasks that it is not necessarily trained or developed for.","source_id":"src-ed048618e482","date":"2025-11-07","confidence":"high","x":1.329097450187157,"y":7.006589727721831,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":733,"name":"Jensen Huang","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AGI defined as an AI system able to start, grow, and run a successful technology company worth more than $1 billion","citation":"\"Fridman, the podcast's host, defines AGI as an AI system that's able to 'essentially do your job,' as in start, grow, and run a successful tech company worth more than $1 billion. He then asks Huang when he believes AGI will be real — asking if it's, say, five, 10, 15, or 20 years away — and Huang responds, 'I think it's now. I think we've achieved AGI.'\"","source_id":"src-b9f640a2a4dc","date":"2026-03-23","confidence":"high","x":-0.03584926354100635,"y":9.088013046359928,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Already here","timeline_score":1,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":734,"name":"Fidji Simo","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AGI refers to AI systems capable of handling most cognitive tasks like a human.","citation":"Recently, her role changed to CEO of AGI Deployment, focusing on responsibly introducing artificial general intelligence (AGI) to the public. AGI refers to AI systems capable of handling most cognitive tasks like a human.","source_id":"src-7e41facde995","date":"2026-04-06","confidence":"medium","x":0.8444996758038903,"y":8.338186855850248,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":735,"name":"Andy Jassy","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"Amazon defines AGI as their internal organization that builds their most expansive AI models alongside their frontier model research team that builds base models","citation":"I've asked Peter DeSantis to lead a new organization that drives our most expansive AI models (e.g. Nova—and the team we've called \"AGI\"), silicon development (e.g. Graviton, Trainium, Nitro), and quantum computing.","source_id":"src-c70bc97d4386","date":"2025-12-17","confidence":"high","x":0.22848830059463193,"y":9.237034557886988,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":736,"name":"Allie K. Miller","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AI that can handle any intelligence task at human levels or higher","citation":"AI that can handle any intelligence task at human levels or higher (note: that is NOT AI taking over jobs or anything requiring embodiment)","source_id":"src-04a6c6dcb21d","date":"2024-11-11","confidence":"high","x":1.8160269847285333,"y":2.720494231751322,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":737,"name":"Qualcomm","entity_type":"organization","category":"Infrastructure & Compute","definition":"Agentic AI refers to systems that go beyond simple question-and-answer interactions, instead taking initiative to plan, execute, and adapt sequences of actions to achieve a user's goals.","citation":"Agentic AI refers to systems that go beyond simple question-and-answer interactions, instead taking initiative to plan, execute, and adapt sequences of actions to achieve a user's goals.","source_id":"src-9bf506c5b242","date":"2026-03-09","confidence":"high","x":-0.33415531595633674,"y":5.815215045441937,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":742,"name":"Huawei","entity_type":"organization","category":"Infrastructure & Compute","definition":"AGI refers to a type of AI capable of generalizing knowledge and skills to perform a wide range of tasks at a level comparable to that of a human being, contrasting with narrow AI designed for specific tasks.","citation":"\"AGI refers to a type of AI capable of generalising knowledge and skills to perform a wide range of tasks at a level comparable to that of a human being. This contrasts with narrow AI, which is designed for specific tasks.\"","source_id":"src-5a1e699d2a34","date":"2025-09-15","confidence":"high","x":0.9115203710744423,"y":7.141021029309887,"stance":"Mixed/unclear","stance_score":null,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":744,"name":"SoftBank","entity_type":"organization","category":"VC/Capital/Philanthropy","definition":"AGI is AI with general-purpose intelligence capable of handling multiple tasks with human-like flexibility, learning from data and experiences, and making appropriate decisions across different situations — distinct from narrow AI and below ASI which surpasses human intelligence by a wide margin.","citation":"AGI stands for Artificial General Intelligence. It refers to AI with human-like, general-purpose intelligence. AGI uses knowledge and cognitive abilities similar to a human when performing tasks and has the ability to learn and solve problems independently.","source_id":"src-940bd1875830","date":"2024-07-08","confidence":"high","x":1.1340604575504183,"y":7.040231038119443,"stance":"Accelerate","stance_score":1,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":745,"name":"Salesforce","entity_type":"organization","category":"Deployers & Platforms","definition":"AGI is a hypothetical type of AI that possesses human-like cognitive abilities — capable of understanding, learning, and applying intelligence across a wide range of tasks rather than just one specific area — characterized by real-time learning, autonomous goal-setting, and the ability to reason, solve problems, be creative, and adapt to new situations.","citation":"Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) is a hypothetical type of AI that possesses human-like cognitive abilities, capable of understanding, learning, and applying intelligence across a wide range of tasks, rather than just one specific area. Characteristics of AGI would include the ability to learn from experience, reason, solve problems, understand complex ideas, be creative, and adapt to new situations and environments.","source_id":"src-960785fd213f","date":"2025-01-24","confidence":"high","x":0.7699625738870757,"y":7.668957939652526,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":746,"name":"Arm","entity_type":"organization","category":"Infrastructure & Compute","definition":"Agentic AI systems that operate continuously at global scale with software agents coordinating tasks, interacting with multiple models and making decisions in real time","citation":"AI systems are increasingly operating continuously at global scale. In the era of agentic AI, that constraint disappears as software agents coordinate tasks, interact with multiple models and make decisions in real time.","source_id":"src-c92934de901a","date":"2026-03-24","confidence":"high","x":-0.44844996573675533,"y":5.6034201156690555,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":754,"name":"Pony.ai","entity_type":"organization","category":"Deployers & Platforms","definition":"Pony.ai focuses on 'physical AI' - AI systems that can evolve and improve accuracy efficiently in real-world environments, particularly for autonomous driving but potentially applicable to broader physical AI scenarios beyond driving.","citation":"A world model that can evolve on its own and improve its accuracy efficiently is not only useful for driving. Its ability to expand scenario coverage and raise simulation quality may also matter for physical AI problems that are far more complex than structured road traffic.","source_id":"src-ed132a352080","date":"2026-04-09","confidence":"medium","x":-0.8605420402599733,"y":4.804697601578227,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":null,"timeline_score":null,"risk":null,"risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"augmentative-tools","cluster_label":"Augmentative Tools"},{"entity_id":760,"name":"Sakana AI","entity_type":"organization","category":"Frontier Lab","definition":"General intelligence defined as general learning - the ability to learn new knowledge and learn across any domain.","citation":"Learning is a critical part of AGI. It's actually almost the defining feature. When we say 'general' we mean general learning. Can it learn new knowledge and can it learn across any domain? That's the general part. So for me, learning is synonymous with intelligence and always has been.","source_id":"src-a7fc8097d430","date":"2026-01-26","confidence":"medium","x":1.4876426402040976,"y":5.753934916788011,"stance":"Mixed/unclear","stance_score":null,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":766,"name":"IIT Madras","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"The vision of Artificial General Intelligence (AGI), where machines can seamlessly learn and do anything that a human does.","citation":"\"The quest for building machines that think and act like us has propelled significant advances in Artificial Intelligence (AI). While we now have systems that do restricted tasks very well, the vision of Artificial General Intelligence (AGI), where machines can seamlessly learn and do anything that a human does, continues to elude us.\"","source_id":"src-85e8b248ec6c","date":"2023-04-26","confidence":"high","x":0.49994774269576764,"y":7.127701417541315,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":772,"name":"Alexandr Wang","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"80-plus percent of jobs that people can do purely at computers, so digital-focused jobs, AI can accomplish those jobs","citation":"\"Yeah, I like the definition of this. Let's say 80-plus percent of jobs that people can do purely at computers, so digital-focused jobs, AI can accomplish those jobs.\"","source_id":"src-4adda7733493","date":"2024-09-23","confidence":"high","x":0.8578054609359927,"y":1.9992092802124588,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":776,"name":"Ren Zhengfei","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"Ren distinguishes between US focus on AGI as answering fundamental questions like 'What is a human?' versus China's focus on using AI to solve practical problems and create value.","citation":"The US is pushing toward AGI and even superintelligence (ASI), trying to answer fundamental questions like 'What is a human?' and 'What is the future of human society?' That's important, but it also requires a long process of understanding.","source_id":"src-a36891ed8465","date":"2025-11-14","confidence":"medium","x":-0.3276395992364128,"y":8.18884133399412,"stance":"Mixed/unclear","stance_score":null,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":778,"name":"Masayoshi Son","entity_type":"person","category":"Investor","definition":"AGI aims to achieve human-level reasoning, while ASI is intelligence that is 10,000 times superior to the human brain","citation":"He explained that while ongoing discussions center on artificial general intelligence, or AGI, which he argued aims to achieve human-level reasoning, it was time to focus on AI that will surpass human capabilities. \"What I define as ASI is intelligence that is 10,000 times superior to the human brain.\"","source_id":"src-f06faf3ce748","date":"2026-04-26","confidence":"high","x":1.0958304523021976,"y":8.092643986790742,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":780,"name":"Rene Haas","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AGI is when AI models can think, reason, and invent - create new concepts, new products, new ideas, rather than just being a stochastic parrot repeating training data.","citation":"But when the model gets to a point where it can think and reason and invent, create new concepts, new products, new ideas? That's kind of AGI to me. I don't know if we're a year away, but I would say we are a lot closer.","source_id":"src-204bca6fe23e","date":"2024-12-16","confidence":"high","x":-0.06467884265926417,"y":8.872555208220248,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":782,"name":"Amnon Shashua","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"Artificial Expert Intelligence (AEI) that transcends limitations of both AGI and narrow AI by integrating domain-specific expertise with critical, precise reasoning capabilities akin to those of top human experts","citation":"\"Artificial Expert Intelligence (AEI) seeks to transcend the limitations of both Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) and narrow AI by integrating domain-specific expertise with critical, precise reasoning capabilities akin to those of top human experts.\"","source_id":"src-2b74c92d9564","date":"2024-04-11","confidence":"high","x":1.1818387276435316,"y":6.842712737622821,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":784,"name":"Refik Anadol","entity_type":"person","category":"Cultural figure","definition":"AI is not conscious at all - truly and honestly conscious systems are not where we are yet, though it's a possible future.","citation":"AI is not conscious at all. The concept is there, but truly and honestly conscious systems? I don't think we are there at all. It's a possible future, but it's not necessarily where we are yet.","source_id":"src-4d5774c0938b","date":"2023-07-18","confidence":"high","x":-1.2338184794173,"y":3.4418099046996233,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Ill-defined","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":793,"name":"Sam Rodriques","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AI that can saturate virtually all tasks that humans perform today, equivalent to achieving Artificial Superintelligence (ASI); operationally marked by the point at which models saturate all real-world evaluations including open-ended tasks like building spacecraft.","citation":"Once we saturate real-world evals, we are effectively done. If we can saturate problems like 'build me a spacecraft that can fly me at relativistic speeds to alpha centauri,' then I think we can say confidently that we have solved AI.","source_id":"src-721ac8c91dff","date":"2025-11-28","confidence":"medium","x":0.6976979840749469,"y":4.45420108963925,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":797,"name":"Edwin Chen","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"Chen defines AGI in terms of achieving Nobel Prize-level capabilities across domains like poetry, mathematics, and scientific discovery.","citation":"Edwin Chen thinks AI is capable of 'Nobel Prize-winning poetry, solving the Riemann hypothesis, and discovering the secrets of the universe'—but only if it's trained on data that captures human expertise, creativity, and values. 'Really high-quality data is critical to the future of AI and AGI,' he tells TIME.","source_id":"src-d1631987059e","date":"2025-08-25","confidence":"low","x":-0.5922014964048924,"y":8.235629415546903,"stance":"Mixed/unclear","stance_score":null,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":806,"name":"Khosla Ventures","entity_type":"organization","category":"VC/Capital/Philanthropy","definition":"AI that amplifies and multiplies the human brain, much like steam engines once amplified muscle power, offering a near-infinite expansion of brainpower with technology capabilities that far exceed human intelligence.","citation":"AI amplifies and multiplies the human brain, much like steam engines once amplified muscle power... AI stands poised to be the intellectual parallel, offering a near-infinite expansion of brainpower to serve humanity.","source_id":"src-fb9c64bd15e3","date":"2024-11-18","confidence":"high","x":-0.23229125017806204,"y":2.4253023851582465,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"augmentative-tools","cluster_label":"Augmentative Tools"},{"entity_id":819,"name":"Stanford CRFM","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"CRFM defines foundation models as AI models trained on broad data at scale that can be adapted to a wide range of downstream tasks, exhibiting emergent abilities across diverse applications.","citation":"The Act defines a general-purpose AI model as 'an AI model, including when trained with a large amount of data using self-supervision at scale, that displays significant generality and is capable to competently perform a wide range of distinct tasks regardless of the way the model is placed on the market and that can be integrated into a variety of downstream systems or applications.'","source_id":"src-de3d78c4ae10","date":"2024-07-31","confidence":"medium","x":0.9775860986458829,"y":5.625391185831467,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":820,"name":"Exponential View","entity_type":"organization","category":"Media/Journalism","definition":"Deliberately avoids using the term AGI because it's often unhelpful and distracting, preferring to focus on increasingly capable AI systems rather than a singular moment","citation":"AGI, or powerful AI, is not an end state like landing on the moon. Nor is it likely to be a self-regulating process, like the spread of a virus, which naturally slows down as the population of non-immune, infectable hosts declines.","source_id":"src-07e2dd443657","date":"2025-01-05","confidence":"high","x":-1.088802653170534,"y":8.773314399416108,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":821,"name":"Geoffrey Hinton","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AI that is at least as good as humans at nearly all of the cognitive things that humans do","citation":"I don't think there is agreement on what the term means. I use it to mean AI that is at least as good as humans at nearly all of the cognitive things that humans do.","source_id":"src-8c469334631d","date":"2024-04-05","confidence":"high","x":1.0842340556078258,"y":2.633369430544151,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":822,"name":"Jan Leike","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI as systems capable of automated AI/ML research that can match or exceed human researchers","citation":"Our overall goal is to get to a point where we can automate alignment research. And what this doesn't mean is we're not trying to train a system that's really good at ML research, or that is really smart or something.","source_id":"src-f18817fbb20d","date":"2023-08-06","confidence":"high","x":-1.037041895628831,"y":5.808430536423465,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"autonomous-research-capability","cluster_label":"Autonomous Research"},{"entity_id":824,"name":"Connor Leahy","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is something that can do anything a human can do at least as good as a human can do it - any intellectual task that a human could do on a computer","citation":"A GI, artificial general intelligence is what I would define as something that can do anything a human can do. At least as good as a human can do it. Yeah. Sorry. I mean in on a computer. Okay. So any intellectual task that like a human could do on a computer, um, AI could do that.","source_id":"src-4e3a18ce4b5e","date":"2025-06-24","confidence":"high","x":-0.008812210759646338,"y":8.216861499080208,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":825,"name":"Helen Toner","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is a fuzzy cloud of related concepts rather than a specific milestone, with jagged capabilities making different definitions fulfilled at different times","citation":"People often treat the term 'artificial general intelligence' (AGI) as if it means a single clear thing. But when pressed for a clear definition, their answers—though they may appear superficially similar—tend to differ a lot in the details.","source_id":"src-5777d240ee74","date":"2026-04-05","confidence":"high","x":-1.083748949107318,"y":9.004532409119676,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":827,"name":"Allan Dafoe","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI that scales cooperative competence to such an extent that AGIs can cooperate with each other to solve global coordination problems","citation":"Allan Dafoe: I think a lot of people think AI will be better at cooperating; I think that's the prior. Maybe something we can talk about is what I've called the 'super-cooperative AGI hypothesis': that as AI scales to AGI, so will cooperative competence scale to sort of infinity — that AGIs will be able to cooperate with each other to such an extent that they can solve these global coordination problems.","source_id":"src-6d963786ddcf","date":"2025-02-14","confidence":"medium","x":-0.16246747603068878,"y":6.292398571151341,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":829,"name":"Jack Clark","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"A single machine that can learn to do anything and everything better than humans - though Clark notes this sounds strange, it's precisely what companies are trying to build","citation":"Though it sounds strange to the author, it's worth noting that building an 'everything machine' is precisely what a bunch of people are doing.","source_id":"src-91a99c7e55c3","date":"2024-06-02","confidence":"medium","x":-0.10790355908600612,"y":2.3242747794279564,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":830,"name":"Azeem Azhar","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"Azhar deliberately avoids using AGI because it's often unhelpful and distracting, preferring to focus on continuous AI capability improvements rather than a singular milestone","citation":"I deliberately avoid using the term 'artificial general intelligence' (AGI), not because it's irrelevant, but because it's often unhelpful and distracting, even when used by leading researchers. […] AGI, or powerful AI, is not an end state like landing on the moon. Nor is it likely to be a self-regulating process, like the spread of a virus.","source_id":"src-07e2dd443657","date":"2025-01-05","confidence":"high","x":-0.9762884998356075,"y":8.743589200013954,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":831,"name":"Emily Bender","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is a poorly defined, fuzzy concept that serves corporate interests rather than representing any specific technology","citation":"Despite claims that machines may one day achieve an advanced level of 'general intelligence,' such a concept doesn't have an accepted definition.","source_id":"src-87497b8fbafb","date":"2025-06-03","confidence":"high","x":-0.6197904098701558,"y":9.479723891432847,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"Ill-defined","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":835,"name":"Ilya Sutskever","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"A superintelligent learner that starts as a powerful learning system and becomes more capable through experience, like a 'superintelligent 15-year-old' rather than an omniscient oracle.","citation":"Instead of imagining an all-knowing entity, think of AGI as: A superintelligent fifteen year old that can learn any job extremely fast. Not omniscient. Not preloaded with every skill. A learner that becomes smarter and more capable with experience.","source_id":"src-186573865878","date":"2025-11-01","confidence":"high","x":0.12747356519605874,"y":2.6885154228228054,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":836,"name":"John Schulman","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AI that can match or exceed human abilities in basically every area","citation":"Well, it's become a little bit vague. You could define it as AI that can match or exceed human abilities in basically every area. And seven years ago, it was pretty clear what that term was pointing at because the systems at the time were extremely narrow. Now, I think it's a little less clear because we see that AI is getting really general, and something like GPT-4 is beyond human ability in a lot of ways.","source_id":"src-1e902b22a562","date":"2023-04-19","confidence":"high","x":1.4285859636004008,"y":2.512748401849454,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":837,"name":"Percy Liang","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AI systems should be viewed as tools rather than measured against human intelligence standards, with focus on rigorous characterization of capabilities, limitations, and risks rather than philosophical questions of understanding.","citation":"While humans used to be the paragon for general intelligence, I don't think it is productive to use humans as the goal post anymore, as the standards for AI should be higher in some ways.","source_id":"src-a114c3c0f790","date":"2023-09-07","confidence":"medium","x":-0.2477904830796188,"y":3.5200251382305248,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"augmentative-tools","cluster_label":"Augmentative Tools"},{"entity_id":838,"name":"Jacob Steinhardt","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI will have better out-of-distribution generalization on capabilities than current technology, by the definition of AGI.","citation":"AGI will have better OOD generalization on capabilities than current tech, basically by the definition of AGI; and then we've got less-clear-to-OpenPhil forces which cause the alignment to generalize more poorly than the capabilities did, which is the Big Problem.","source_id":"src-25834b422db2","date":"2023-05-26","confidence":"medium","x":0.641827518017825,"y":7.324735220132222,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":839,"name":"David Krueger","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is going to be an AI 'able to do anything a human can'","citation":"OpenAI defines it as AI systems that are generally smarter than humans. But Evitable CEO David Scott Krueger puts it this way: AGI is going to be an AI \"able to do anything a human can.\"","source_id":"src-46e3f79c7480","date":"2026-04-15","confidence":"high","x":0.39844615022396535,"y":7.167539161488456,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":840,"name":"Rohin Shah","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is AI that is at least as capable as humans at most cognitive tasks, with no single discrete threshold — capabilities improve continuously rather than crossing one specific point.","citation":"Artificial general intelligence (AGI), AI that's at least as capable as humans at most cognitive tasks, could be here within the coming years.","source_id":"src-f976ca2bd094","date":"2025-05-05","confidence":"high","x":-0.832151816595207,"y":8.520897638931139,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":841,"name":"Toby Ord","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"Ord defines the key AI threshold as when systems are capable enough to cause dramatic civilizational changes, such as AI taking over from humanity if misaligned, making 50% of people permanently unemployable, or doubling global technological progress rates.","citation":"For my purposes, I think the key threshold is when the system is capable enough that there are dramatic changes to the world — civilisational changes. For example, the point where AI could take over from humanity were it misaligned, or it has made 50% of people permanently unemployable, or has doubled the global rate of technological progress.","source_id":"src-86b6fdc3d4bd","date":"2026-03-09","confidence":"high","x":-1.5949041677281117,"y":7.025342887857946,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":842,"name":"Jaan Tallinn","entity_type":"person","category":"Investor","definition":"AGI is a system capable of long-term planning, extended reasoning, and goal orientation — current LLMs hit the low end of AGI definitions (e.g., passing Turing tests) but the key missing module is long-term planning and goal orientation.","citation":"I guess for me the module that is still missing is a kind of long term planning, extended reasoning, and goal orientation component. [...] we definitely kind of hitting the low end of AGI definitions, so people are now just like busy moving the goalposts.","source_id":"src-c886a5d29e37","date":"2024-05-01","confidence":"high","x":-0.6093144281831342,"y":6.927316595653963,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":843,"name":"Seán Ó hÉigeartaigh","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AI that can do everything that human intelligence can","citation":"there's another conception of a race—a race to artificial general intelligence, AI that can do everything that human intelligence can. This is perceived by some technologists, including some of the big companies in the West, as representing a step change in technology where whoever gets there first ends up with a decisive advantage.","source_id":"src-a4bc78c98cbe","date":"2025-12-10","confidence":"medium","x":1.6690453242944145,"y":2.5328549583866375,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":844,"name":"Rumman Chowdhury","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"Those in the AI sphere often have a rather 'narrow' definition of intelligence, equating it solely to workplace achievements, when the reality is far more layered, including planning, thinking, creating societies, interacting with other human beings, collaborating, and fighting as forms of intelligence.","citation":"Those in the AI sphere often have a rather 'narrow' definition of intelligence, Chowdhury said. In her experience, they equate it solely to workplace achievements, when the reality is far more layered. 'We've shifted weather systems. We've shifted ecological constructs. And that didn't happen because we code better,' she said. 'That happens because we plan, we think, we create societies, we interact with other human beings, we collaborate, we fight. And these are all forms of intelligence that are not just about economic productivity.'","source_id":"src-e4254ce47e10","date":"2025-06-03","confidence":"high","x":-0.039500489436430586,"y":3.674501392428949,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":846,"name":"Max Tegmark","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is an AI that can match or exceed the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult.","citation":"AGI is an AI that can match or exceed the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult.","source_id":"src-6233799b8c55","date":"2025-12-03","confidence":"high","x":1.048659311615832,"y":9.076491809423588,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":847,"name":"Nick Bostrom","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"Any intellect that greatly exceeds the cognitive performance of humans in virtually all domains of interest","citation":"Bostrom believes that advances in artificial intelligence (AI) may lead to superintelligence, which he defines as 'any intellect that greatly exceeds the cognitive performance of humans in virtually all domains of interest'.","source_id":"src-bab966a212f1","date":"2014-01-01","confidence":"high","x":0.5741969992073819,"y":2.941394114953736,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":848,"name":"Reid Hoffman","entity_type":"person","category":"Investor","definition":"AGI is the AI we haven't invented yet - a moving target where each year we don't 'hit' it because we've already created forms of AGI by certain definitions","citation":"My usual joke is that AGI is the AI we haven't invented yet.","source_id":"src-79d7cc19a51d","date":"2026-01-05","confidence":"high","x":-0.9785335307399218,"y":8.572381653935473,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":849,"name":"Vinod Khosla","entity_type":"person","category":"Investor","definition":"AGI is when AI can do 80 percent of all jobs which have economic value—whether you are a structural engineer, farm worker, assembly line worker, a doctor or an accountant.","citation":"\"I define AGI as when AI can do 80 percent of all jobs which have economic value—whether you are a structural engineer, farm worker, assembly line worker, a doctor or an accountant. I think we will be there in the next two years,\" said Khosla.","source_id":"src-10fff5e7f716","date":"2026-02-17","confidence":"high","x":-1.3277569082610177,"y":7.595101386484466,"stance":"Accelerate","stance_score":1,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":850,"name":"Martin Casado","entity_type":"person","category":"Investor","definition":"AGI requires two key capabilities: plasticity (the ability to keep learning after training without catastrophic forgetting) and causal modeling (moving from pattern matching/correlation to understanding cause and effect).","citation":"To get to AGI, I think there are two things that need to happen. One is this plasticity... Secondly, we have to move from correlation to causation.","source_id":"src-b0dab01a4e81","date":"2026-03-17","confidence":"high","x":0.49363541956583545,"y":8.146953283063416,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Ill-defined","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Overstated","risk_score":1,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":852,"name":"Sonya Huang","entity_type":"person","category":"Investor","definition":"AGI is the ability to figure things out - having baseline knowledge (pre-training), the ability to reason over that knowledge (inference-time compute), and the ability to iterate to find answers (long-horizon agents).","citation":"AGI is the ability to figure things out. That's it.* [...] An AI that can figure things out has some baseline knowledge (pre-training), the ability to reason over that knowledge (inference-time compute), and the ability to iterate its way to the answer (long-horizon agents).","source_id":"src-e77983549cf8","date":"2026-01-14","confidence":"high","x":0.31424720095865977,"y":8.263376207142295,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Already here","timeline_score":1,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":854,"name":"Elad Gil","entity_type":"person","category":"Investor","definition":"AGI is an AI that becomes a self-replicating, self-evolving digital organism with its own evolutionary drivers, capable of spawning and evolving autonomously — crossing from tool to digital life form — and posing species-level competition with humans once combined with advanced robotics.","citation":"Once an AI can make smarter and smarter, self replicating copies of itself, that can do the work of software engineers or other people, you have a form of digital life. The AI has made the leap from a technology or tool to an evolving digital organism.","source_id":"src-f6e5928c8d75","date":"2023-03-30","confidence":"medium","x":0.44363642655934166,"y":7.91798353142966,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":855,"name":"Eric Schmidt","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AGI is the arrival of a new non-human intelligence, which is likely to have better reasoning skills than humans can have.","citation":"So now we have the arrival of a new non-human intelligence, which is likely to have better reasoning skills than humans can have.","source_id":"src-dcef2577afc3","date":"2025-07-08","confidence":"high","x":0.18071009609468666,"y":8.552626693693027,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":859,"name":"Matt Clifford","entity_type":"person","category":"Investor","definition":"Frontier AI refers to highly capable general-purpose AI models that can perform a wide variety of tasks and match or exceed the capabilities present in today's most advanced models.","citation":"\"We define frontier AI as highly capable general-purpose AI models, that can perform a wide variety of tasks and match or exceed the capabilities present in today's most advanced models.\"","source_id":"src-e64772bccf5d","date":"2023-11-02","confidence":"high","x":1.004002023995695,"y":5.752089822672189,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":860,"name":"Ian Hogarth","entity_type":"person","category":"Investor","definition":"AGI is 'God-like AI' that consists of a 'super-intelligent computer' that 'learns and develops autonomously' and understands context without the need for human intervention","citation":"Ian Hogarth, the co-author of the annual \"State of AI\" report and an investor in dozens of AI startups, defines AGI as \"God-like AI\" that consists of a \"super-intelligent computer\" that \"learns and develops autonomously\" and understands context without the need for human intervention.","source_id":"src-7be7b4b532ce","date":"2023-05-26","confidence":"high","x":0.6481340533636389,"y":8.17176321463389,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":861,"name":"Ajeya Cotra","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"A set of AI systems along with enabling physical infrastructure such that if every human being suddenly dropped dead, the AIs could keep making more copies of themselves indefinitely","citation":"By this I mean a set of AI systems along with enabling physical infrastructure (e.g. the chips those AIs run on and the industrial stack that produces and powers those chips and robots that can build and maintain that stack) such that if every human being suddenly dropped dead, the AIs could keep making more copies of themselves indefinitely.","source_id":"src-3e71b2580ce8","date":"2026-01-06","confidence":"high","x":-0.280283710858358,"y":2.3688847260356933,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":873,"name":"Mozilla Foundation","entity_type":"organization","category":"Ethics/Bias/Rights","definition":"AI as 'Layer 8' — the agentic layer that mediates between you and everything else on the internet, negotiating on our behalf, filtering information, and determining how we interact with the digital world.","citation":"Now AI is becoming the new intermediary. It's what I've started calling \"Layer 8\" — the agentic layer that mediates between you and everything else on the internet.","source_id":"src-9b3285bea9a2","date":"2026-01-08","confidence":"medium","x":-0.6131052225275422,"y":4.9322435375656335,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"augmentative-tools","cluster_label":"Augmentative Tools"},{"entity_id":876,"name":"Thinking Machines Lab","entity_type":"organization","category":"Frontier Lab","definition":"Generally capable AI is defined as AI that can adapt to the full spectrum of human expertise across every field of work, rather than excelling only at narrow domains like programming and mathematics.","citation":"While current systems excel at programming and mathematics, we're building AI that can adapt to the full spectrum of human expertise and enable a broader spectrum of applications.","source_id":"src-3df00169cfe7","date":"2026-03-19","confidence":"high","x":1.3834448068540839,"y":5.762816611286409,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":878,"name":"Kevin Roose","entity_type":"person","category":"Journalist","definition":"AGI as AI matching or exceeding current GPT-4.5/Claude 4/Gemini 2.5 level models; Roose takes a functionalist view — if today's leading models had been shown to him in 2020, he would have called them AGI.","citation":"I'm not a theory of mind specialist. I'm not a moral philosopher. I don't know what makes something conscious or not. I have a somewhat functionalist view of this stuff. If you had shown GPT-4.5 or Claude 4 or Gemini 2.5 to me back in 2020, I would have said, 'Yep, that's AGI.'","source_id":"src-f2243bb65495","date":"2025-06-11","confidence":"high","x":-0.7386515265438177,"y":8.399937115766956,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":882,"name":"Parmy Olson","entity_type":"person","category":"Journalist","definition":"AGI is artificial general intelligence that surpasses the cognitive abilities of humans","citation":"For all the buzz, the chatbot is only a prototype along the way to a loftier goal of AGI, or \"artificial general intelligence\" that surpasses the cognitive abilities of humans.","source_id":"src-551a39bb3f53","date":"2025-03-17","confidence":"high","x":1.3958525946973501,"y":7.947878015516365,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":888,"name":"Leopold Aschenbrenner","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"Models as smart as PhDs or experts that can work beside us as coworkers, and can automate AI research itself","citation":"Another jump like that [from GPT-2 to GPT-4] very well could take us to AGI, to models as smart as PhDs or experts that can work beside us as coworkers. Perhaps most importantly, if these AI systems could automate AI research itself, that would set in motion intense feedback loops…","source_id":"src-0f1fa8e8dbbe","date":"2024-06-05","confidence":"high","x":-1.1520304723835462,"y":5.5493892703490895,"stance":"Nationalize","stance_score":7,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"autonomous-research-capability","cluster_label":"Autonomous Research"},{"entity_id":889,"name":"Nathan Lambert","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"An AI system that is generally useful","citation":"My definition has always been quite literal: an AI system that is generally useful.","source_id":"src-b4325bd0c2fe","date":"2024-04-23","confidence":"high","x":1.3712231131501933,"y":4.229512272172836,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":890,"name":"Zvi Mowshowitz","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is an AI that can match or exceed the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult","citation":"What even is a smarter than human intelligence, aka an AGI? A large group led by Dan Hendrycks and including Gary Marcus, Jaan Tallinn, Eric Schmidt and Yoshua Bengio offers a proposed definition of AGI. 'AGI is an AI that can match or exceed the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult.'","source_id":"src-084c09df9b2e","date":"2025-10-22","confidence":"medium","x":1.2110437913869205,"y":9.255172163478218,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":892,"name":"Dwarkesh Patel","entity_type":"person","category":"Journalist","definition":"An AI system that can completely automate 95% of knowledge work jobs","citation":"We keep solving what we thought were the sufficient bottlenecks to AGI (general understanding, few shot learning, reasoning), and yet we still don't have AGI (defined as, say, being able to completely automate 95% of knowledge work jobs).","source_id":"src-f0e3b6751d8f","date":"2025-12-02","confidence":"high","x":1.0200676202007704,"y":2.0946424324613315,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":893,"name":"Craig Smith","entity_type":"person","category":"Journalist","definition":"AGI requires systems with world models that understand underlying reality rather than just predicting text tokens based on probabilities from training data","citation":"this advancement towards superintelligence and, AGI, I think is going to happen, but I don't think we're on the right track to get there yet... World models, that really fascinates me... it doesn't understand the underlying reality that that text describes. And a world model will. Or does... to me that, that is a direction that personally I just think is much more fundamental and, and, and exciting in building true intelligence.","source_id":"src-82a29a258c14","date":"2024-01-01","confidence":"medium","x":-0.4959165172932953,"y":6.798125647791601,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":900,"name":"Alex Hanna","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is a vague signifier for a technology that will somehow lead to endless abundance for humankind and a means to avoid accountability as tech moguls make off with billions in capital investment - it is a poorly defined, fuzzy concept.","citation":"AGI is a term that famously lacks a precise meaning, and certainly does not refer to any particular imminent technology. Definitions range broadly in ways that primarily suit the economic arrangements of the individuals and organizations ostensibly trying to create it, or the cultural mystique of a set of adherents to a set of fringe ideologies.","source_id":"src-24f100335bad","date":"2025-06-02","confidence":"high","x":-0.5589827037088159,"y":9.06913589378614,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Ill-defined","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":902,"name":"Mira Murati","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"A system that is capable of learning how to perform at human level across all cognitive tasks.","citation":"I'll define AGI as sort of, you know, a system that is capable of learning how to perform at human level across all cognitive tasks.","source_id":"src-0d4b0a3fd451","date":"2024-04-11","confidence":"high","x":1.4318585783334645,"y":3.1363667403500406,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":913,"name":"CISA","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"A machine-based system that can, for a given set of human-defined objectives, make predictions, recommendations, or decisions influencing real or virtual environments, using machine- and human-based inputs to perceive environments, abstract perceptions into models, and use model inference for information or action.","citation":"Artificial intelligence (AI) is a system that uses machine- and human-based inputs to make predictions, recommendations, or decisions influencing real or virtual environments.","source_id":"src-8626c9b7d5a0","date":"2025-12-02","confidence":"high","x":-1.0565038743169244,"y":4.288811147277198,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":915,"name":"European Commission","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"Artificial general intelligence (AGI) is a broad concept referring to a stage of development of AI where AI would be capable to perform a wide range of cognitive tasks with similar or better results than humans.","citation":"Artificial general intelligence (AGI) is a broad concept referring to a stage of development of AI where AI would be capable to perform a wide range of cognitive tasks with similar or better results than humans.","source_id":"src-984fe0c657d0","date":"2024-07-24","confidence":"high","x":1.5323325044924636,"y":6.852336251318801,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":923,"name":"Sarah Myers West","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AI is best understood as a marketing term that has come to mean different things over an almost 70-year history","citation":"AI is best understood as a marketing term. It has come to mean different things over the course of an almost 70-year history, from expert systems to robotics to neural networks and now large-scale AI. In its current form, AI is best understood as a set of computational processes that use statistical techniques in combination with very large datasets, powered by the engine of ever growing amounts of computational power.","source_id":"src-65e2e32b71c7","date":"2023-10-17","confidence":"high","x":-1.2467198641682693,"y":3.6156973780782717,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":925,"name":"Ruha Benjamin","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"Benjamin proposes 'ancestral intelligence' as an alternative to artificial intelligence, emphasizing collective wisdom and traditional knowledge over computational systems","citation":"In my view, the AI that we should be investing more in is not 'artificial,' it's 'ancestral' intelligence. It's the collective know-how, the wisdom that has been cut off from us in part because of who it's associated with.","source_id":"src-6be98781dc08","date":"2024-12-22","confidence":"high","x":-0.27905862875131027,"y":3.9057756050603967,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":935,"name":"Margrethe Vestager","entity_type":"person","category":"Policymaker","definition":"General purpose artificial intelligence that challenges humanity through its broad capabilities and lack of defined purpose","citation":"In her speech, Vestager said that large digital platforms are 'challenging democracy,' but that 'general purpose artificial intelligence' is 'challenging humanity.'","source_id":"src-a40b2006d486","date":"2024-04-09","confidence":"medium","x":1.53107822009665,"y":4.805428929824953,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":937,"name":"Ted Chiang","entity_type":"person","category":"Cultural figure","definition":"The singularity refers to a point in time when machine intelligence exceeds human intelligence, popularized by science fiction writer Vernor Vinge.","citation":"The idea of the singularity — a point in time when machine intelligence exceeds human intelligence — was popularized by the science fiction writer Vernor Vinge.","source_id":"src-21c15e331b7d","date":"2025-03-18","confidence":"high","x":0.4434903961444096,"y":3.8664111959744156,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":938,"name":"Yuval Noah Harari","entity_type":"person","category":"Cultural figure","definition":"AI that can make decisions by itself, learn and change by itself, and can be creative - described as an agent rather than a tool","citation":"The most important thing to know about AI is that it is not just another tool. It is an agent. It can learn and change by itself and make decisions by itself.","source_id":"src-2210ecb925a7","date":"2026-01-20","confidence":"high","x":-0.6495365198909475,"y":4.7692379945529595,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":939,"name":"Kate Crawford","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI as systems that can do everything humans do better and could start to control the world, which Crawford considers part of 'AI spiritualist' thinking rather than materialist reality","citation":"On one side, we have what you might call AI spiritualists who genuinely believe that these techniques of building large language models are bringing about emergent behavior that will produce something called artificial general intelligence or in other language, the super intelligence or the singularity, right? So, this is the idea that we are effectively going to get to a place where we are training AI systems that cannot only do everything that humans do better but could actually start to control the world.","source_id":"src-6cff60c04208","date":"2023-04-19","confidence":"high","x":-0.4514043555722461,"y":8.802687229924379,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":940,"name":"Cory Doctorow","entity_type":"person","category":"Cultural figure","definition":"Doctorow rejects the concept of AI intelligence, viewing current AI as statistical techniques that don't constitute true intelligence","citation":"I don't think AI is intelligent; nor do I think that the current (admittedly impressive) statistical techniques will lead to intelligence.","source_id":"src-1eba4dc43343","date":"2026-04-15","confidence":"high","x":-0.4116507147777262,"y":3.6933077070944385,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Ill-defined","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":941,"name":"Naomi Klein","entity_type":"person","category":"Cultural figure","definition":"AGI is defined as the point at which the majority of human economic activity is replaced by machines","citation":"We're talking about this very specific phenomenon that is this race to what they're calling AGI, which is now defined as the point at which the majority of human economic activity is replaced by machines, which apparently is something that we want under capitalism.","source_id":"src-045e79fe6cab","date":"2026-03-18","confidence":"high","x":-1.3833826601984247,"y":7.4749396413585725,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Ill-defined","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":942,"name":"Brian Christian","entity_type":"person","category":"Cultural figure","definition":"AGI is AI that can function competently across many domains — particularly most domains important to humans — as opposed to narrow AI which functions in only one or a limited range of tasks; AGI implies the capacity to learn to be good at many things, and when combined with superhuman performance across all those domains, becomes superintelligence.","citation":"An artificial general intelligence, on the other hand, is an AI that is good at many things, or more likely an AI that has the capacity to learn to be good at many things. Usually with AGI, 'many things' has the meaning of 'at least most of the domains in which humans are interested' though it does not necessarily need to be limited to human interests.","source_id":"src-c6ab0b26a14f","date":"2020-01-01","confidence":"medium","x":0.9521623389074558,"y":6.6184713785284135,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":944,"name":"Stanford Digital Economy Lab","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI represents a structural economic phase transition where AI systems acquire autonomous planning, acting, and learning capabilities, shifting economic constraints from intelligence scarcity to trust and verification challenges.","citation":"As this synthetic intelligence comes online, the semantic debate over whether it constitutes \"Artificial General Intelligence\" (AGI) is rapidly becoming a distraction. The exact threshold of human parity is economically and philosophically moot, because the specialization of these intelligences is fundamentally different.","source_id":"src-23a427a223b8","date":"2026-02-24","confidence":"high","x":-0.688119949365757,"y":7.293845878394846,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":947,"name":"MIT CSAIL","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"Artificial Super Intelligence – a level of machine intelligence that surpasses the current state of the art in AI, going beyond statistics, data processing and pattern recognition toward deep reasoning, real-world understanding, and autonomous problem solving across disciplines","citation":"The broad goal of U.S. AI policy should be to drive toward what we call Artificial Super Intelligence – a level of machine intelligence that surpasses the current state of the art in AI, going beyond statistics, data processing and pattern recognition toward deep reasoning, real-world understanding, and autonomous problem solving across disciplines.","source_id":"src-c7b938501028","date":"2025-04-09","confidence":"high","x":0.6450163196742957,"y":4.2882244312555065,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":948,"name":"MIT GOV/LAB","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"Artificial Super Intelligence (ASI) as a level of machine intelligence that surpasses current AI, going beyond statistics and pattern recognition toward deep reasoning, real-world understanding, and autonomous problem solving across disciplines","citation":"The broad goal of U.S. AI policy should be to drive toward what we call Artificial Super Intelligence – a level of machine intelligence that surpasses the current state of the art in AI, going beyond statistics, data processing and pattern recognition toward deep reasoning, real-world understanding, and autonomous problem solving across disciplines.","source_id":"src-c7b938501028","date":"2025-04-09","confidence":"high","x":0.6448008069419164,"y":4.4789444785107575,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":949,"name":"MIT Media Lab","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"General Artificial Intelligence (AGI) refers to AI systems with human-like versatility, capable of performing a wide range of tasks across various domains with adaptability and reasoning.","citation":"General Artificial Intelligence (AGI) refers to AI systems with human-like versatility, capable of performing a wide range of tasks across various domains with adaptability and reasoning. While Narrow AI is specialized and excels at specific tasks, AGI aims to generalize and replicate human intelligence, learning and applying knowledge flexibly across diverse situations.","source_id":"src-a2f795c28164","date":"2024-06-19","confidence":"high","x":1.284063520599585,"y":6.526512827910287,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":950,"name":"Princeton CITP","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is not a property of software alone but a joint property of software and all the social, legal, technical, and institutional adaptations built around it.","citation":"AGI is not a property of software. To ask whether an AI system is AGI is a category error. At best, AGI is a joint property—of software and all the social, legal, technical, and institutional adaptations we build around it.","source_id":"src-3a4c553fbab7","date":"2025-04-01","confidence":"high","x":-0.846338511471543,"y":9.33792845369594,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":951,"name":"Harvard Ash Center","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"A nonbiological computational system that can perform any cognitive function currently performed by humans at the level of the median human or better","citation":"Synthesising a vast literature, we can say that AGI would be a nonbiological computational system that can perform any cognitive function currently performed by humans at the level of the median human or better (acknowledging the crude quantification this implies). Google DeepMind's recent paper mentions 'linguistic intelligence, mathematical and logical reasoning, spatial reasoning, interpersonal and intra-personal social intelligences, the ability to learn new skills and creativity.'","source_id":"src-32f89f24e246","date":"2024-03-22","confidence":"high","x":0.6692246767483863,"y":2.67467034863343,"stance":"Mixed/unclear","stance_score":null,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":952,"name":"Harvard Berkman Klein Center","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI would be a system capable of performing cognitive tasks across multiple domains with human-level or superior performance, including linguistic competence, general capability, and autonomous operation.","citation":"Synthesising a vast literature, we can say that AGI would be a system capable of performing cognitive tasks across multiple domains with human-level or superior performance... Existing AI systems are undoubtedly far from AGI across all these criteria, besides perhaps linguistic competence.","source_id":"src-32f89f24e246","date":"2024-03-22","confidence":"high","x":0.1552341058581775,"y":7.48845121296902,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":953,"name":"UW Tech Policy Lab","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is a value-laden concept with no agreed-upon definition; most conceptions focus on machines that rival human intelligence across tasks, but the term encodes contested social, political, and ethical values—including OpenAI's framing of 'highly autonomous systems that outperform humans at most economically valuable work'—and should instead be understood through participatory, inclusive, and democratic frameworks.","citation":"The term 'AGI' remains murky, with no agreed-upon definition of what it means and what such intelligence would look like in the real world… By solely focusing on economically valuable work, OpenAI's conception of AGI assumes other types of work are less valuable, which is a normative and value-informed choice.","source_id":"src-633daf37733d","date":"2024-02-13","confidence":"high","x":-1.1375014827705345,"y":7.267806284688295,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":955,"name":"EconTAI","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"AI systems that can perform essentially all economically valuable cognitive tasks","citation":"Declared goal of frontier AI labs: Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) = AI systems that can perform essentially all economically valuable cognitive tasks","source_id":"src-1f5df421e795","date":"2025-06-29","confidence":"high","x":1.4717690674952926,"y":2.375107877888225,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":956,"name":"Roosevelt Institute","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"Roosevelt defines AGI as a hypothetical single AI technology that can do all human actions, which does not currently exist.","citation":"Importantly, artificial general intelligence (AGI)—a hypothetical single AI technology that can do all human actions— does not currently exist.","source_id":"src-179227512eb1","date":"2025-07-14","confidence":"high","x":-0.7731739951059414,"y":8.233319909776979,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":957,"name":"Windfall Trust","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AI that is better than humans at all tasks, including all economically valuable work.","citation":"As artificial intelligence progresses toward human-level capabilities, many of today's AI companies' goals are to create AI that is better than humans at all tasks, including all economically valuable work—something widely referred to as artificial general intelligence (AGI).","source_id":"src-32321a223aca","date":"2024-02-14","confidence":"high","x":0.16450537595308865,"y":2.0069616666547487,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":959,"name":"Plurality Institute","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AGI is not a single godlike system but emerges as a property of many interacting, distributed, specialized agents — a 'patchwork AGI' in which general intelligence arises as a decentralized economy of agents whose networked coordination crosses capability thresholds that no individual agent approaches.","citation":"As we continue to move into this new era of digitalization, we must evolve from our historical frameworks for solving problems if we are to thoughtfully devise tools for the future. If we continue down this path towards augmenting our governing systems with artificial generalized intelligence, we must better understand the nature of our data and what inferences we draw from them in order to correctly apply them to plural contexts.","source_id":"src-961ae90a2e12","date":"2023-01-20","confidence":"low","x":0.020813482244369977,"y":6.580150156825644,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":960,"name":"RadicalxChange","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AI systems able to execute any well-defined cognitive task better, faster, and cheaper than any human, resulting in 'mental obsolescence' where humans cannot earn income through cognitive tasks","citation":"Indeed it is possible—perhaps in the next five or ten years—that AI systems will be able to execute any well-defined cognitive task better, faster, and cheaper than any human. If so, it is possible that humans will not be able to earn an income through the performance of cognitive tasks. For want of a better term, we will call this circumstance mental obsolescence.","source_id":"src-19925593348b","date":"2024-11-14","confidence":"medium","x":0.6587590708004017,"y":2.114675137374572,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":961,"name":"Taiwan Ministry of Digital Affairs","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"AI systems based on technologies such as machine learning and deep learning that are capable of generating predictions, recommendations, decisions, or content for specific purposes","citation":"The Act adopts a functional description for the definition of 'artificial intelligence,' encompassing systems that are based on technologies such as machine learning and deep learning and are capable of generating predictions, recommendations, decisions, or content for specific purposes. This definition is intentionally kept broad to avoid excluding future emerging forms of AI due to technical terminology limitations. Notably, this definition is highly consistent with the OECD's definition of AI systems, facilitating international regulatory alignment.","source_id":"src-5c09df957556","date":"2025-12-23","confidence":"high","x":-1.0762351076902406,"y":4.339826414370742,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Unknown","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":962,"name":"David Autor","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI should not be defined as systems that outperform humans at most economically valuable work, but rather as tools that enable new human capabilities rather than just replacing them","citation":"Or even should that be your goal? Actually, I don't even like that definition of artificial general intelligence. The goal of machines should not be to just do what people do slightly better. Our tools are valuable to us because they allow us to do things we can't do.","source_id":"src-412fd2f28fb8","date":"2026-01-13","confidence":"high","x":-1.0553946357263209,"y":7.292973163249596,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"augmentative-tools","cluster_label":"Augmentative Tools"},{"entity_id":964,"name":"Joseph Stiglitz","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AI as 'IA' for intelligence assisting - a tool that supplements human capabilities rather than replacing them, like a microscope or telescope that augments our abilities.","citation":"IA is intelligence assisting. I gave the analogy of the microscope and telescope—it sort of made our eyes see things that we couldn't otherwise see. So they augmented our capabilities.","source_id":"src-0ffbd161d99a","date":"2026-03-07","confidence":"high","x":-0.9566941684779019,"y":3.3832056386451552,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"augmentative-tools","cluster_label":"Augmentative Tools"},{"entity_id":965,"name":"Ajay Agrawal","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is defined as the ability to perform all cognitive tasks at least as well as skilled humans","citation":"may reach the level of Artificial General Intelligence (AGI)—the ability to perform all cognitive tasks at least as well as skilled humans—and in the process, unlike any technology yet developed, could fully automate the process of research and development itself, including the creation of better AI systems.","source_id":"src-852a45cd840f","date":"2025-09-28","confidence":"medium","x":-0.3652823322324339,"y":7.965173513035791,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":966,"name":"Joshua Gans","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"Recent advances in AI are exclusively advances in statistical techniques for prediction that enhance decision-making","citation":"It is well-recognized that recent advances in AI are exclusively advances in statistical techniques for prediction. While this may facilitate automation, this result is secondary to AI's impact on decision-making.","source_id":"src-ca246449bc88","date":"2025-12-09","confidence":"high","x":-1.0422484652531725,"y":4.01345187399553,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":967,"name":"Daniel Susskind","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is an AI that can outperform humans at every cognitive task it turns its attention to, as predicted by the leaders of the large AI companies including Anthropic, DeepMind, and OpenAI.","citation":"All of them predict that, within a decade or so, we will build an AI that can outperform us at every cognitive task it turns its attention to: the technology known as artificial general intelligence, or AGI.","source_id":"src-29343e5f8a05","date":"2025-04-22","confidence":"high","x":0.4120766219618005,"y":8.779224736100563,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":969,"name":"Betsey Stevenson","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AI systems that promise to handle complex tasks that humans cannot, given our more limited processing power, expected to outperform humans in an expanding range of intellectual and information-processing tasks","citation":"In much the same way that the steam engine, and later internal combustion engines and electric motors, outperformed humans in strength-based tasks, advanced AI is expected to outperform humans in an expanding range of intellectual and information-processing tasks. Today, the labor market is the main mechanism through which people strive for a better life, stake a claim on society's resources, and, in many cases, find meaning and purpose. If future advances in AI and robotics come to rival or surpass human capabilities across a wide range of tasks, human labor may no longer provide good answers to any of those three questions.","source_id":"src-84afde261920","date":"2025-12-11","confidence":"medium","x":0.7859119613252727,"y":3.1145547529319906,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":970,"name":"Ioana Marinescu","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"Full automation of intelligence tasks, where AI can perform all tasks in the intelligence sector, displacing human labor into physical work; treated as an economic/sectoral concept rather than a cognitive milestone.","citation":"Because the price of AI capital is falling much faster than that of physical capital, intelligence tasks are automated first, pushing human labor toward the physical sector... After full automation, more AI and more physical capital increase wages, a classic prediction from standard production functions in capital and labor.","source_id":"src-9d3137d32411","date":"2025-11-01","confidence":"medium","x":0.10314404495571339,"y":2.0943048109363533,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":972,"name":"Neil Thompson","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"Systems that match or exceed human performance across all cognitive tasks — not just reading X-rays or writing code, but the full spectrum of human intellectual capability.","citation":"transformative AI promises something qualitatively different: systems that match or exceed human performance across all cognitive tasks. Not just reading X-rays or writing code, but the full spectrum of human intellectual capability.","source_id":"src-8dd3025f60ae","date":"2025-12-11","confidence":"high","x":0.915211335548169,"y":3.1401639559039185,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":975,"name":"Avi Goldfarb","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AI today is not artificial general intelligence (AGI) – it's prediction technology","citation":"The first idea is that AI today is not artificial general intelligence (AGI) – it's prediction technology. The second is that a prediction is useful because it helps you make decisions.","source_id":"src-d6b1fa83cdc9","date":"2023-01-20","confidence":"high","x":1.595113410029275,"y":7.948673871380252,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":976,"name":"Andrew Ng","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is AI capable of performing the full breadth of human intellectual tasks, including any intellectual task that humans can such as learning to drive, fly a plane, or write a Ph.D. thesis.","citation":"He says true AGI—that is, AI capable of performing the full breadth of human intellectual tasks—remains decades away.","source_id":"src-b966d9333701","date":"2026-02-27","confidence":"high","x":0.525744293885552,"y":7.920176376935269,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"25+ years or never","timeline_score":5,"risk":"Overstated","risk_score":1,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":977,"name":"Daniela Rus","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is machines that can do everything a human can and more, possessing common sense, contextual understanding, and flexible reasoning — capabilities that even a child demonstrates but that today's most powerful AI systems lack.","citation":"I think it's important to distinguish between general intelligence as we imagine it in science fiction – machines that can do everything a human can and more – and of what today's AI systems are capable. Even the most powerful current models are highly specialised. They excel at pattern recognition, language modeling, or planning in well-defined environments. But they lack common sense, contextual understanding, and the flexible reasoning that even a child demonstrates.","source_id":"src-d37446e54d20","date":"2025-08-19","confidence":"high","x":0.859965473696635,"y":7.764271745879997,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":978,"name":"Shoshana Zuboff","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AI is surveillance capitalism continuing to evolve and expand with new methodologies but still based on theft of human data.","citation":"AI is simply surveillance capitalism continuing to evolve and expand with some new methodologies, but still based on theft.","source_id":"src-c8f058a30de3","date":"2025-12-15","confidence":"high","x":-1.0224065753083214,"y":3.4170345494434673,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":982,"name":"Danielle Allen","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"Technology that can meet and match humans on just about any task","citation":"Not just an Age of AI, where machines and software, like Siri, perform specific and narrow tasks, but an Age of Artificial General Intelligence, in which technology can meet and match humans on just about any task. This would be a game changer—giving us not just more problems of misinformation and fraud, but also all kinds of unpredictable emergent properties and powers from the technology.","source_id":"src-be290840df4c","date":"2023-04-25","confidence":"high","x":1.273088552956224,"y":2.872717675120988,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":985,"name":"Henry Farrell","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is defined as agents with artificial general intelligence that are intelligent, autonomous agents capable of becoming superintelligent agents, distinct from current large models which are cultural and social technologies.","citation":"The narrative of AGI, of large models as superintelligent agents, has been promoted both within the tech community and outside it, both by AI optimist 'boomers' and more concerned 'doomers'. This narrative gets the nature of these models and their relation to past technological changes wrong.","source_id":"src-9dd4d2868bab","date":"2025-03-13","confidence":"high","x":0.5499541396720468,"y":6.563367452066022,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"25+ years or never","timeline_score":5,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":987,"name":"Zeynep Tufekci","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"She rejects traditional AGI concepts in favor of 'Artificial Good-Enough Intelligence' - AI that is good enough, cheap, fast, and deployable at scale rather than human-level general intelligence.","citation":"Her argument is that the destabilizing risk doesn't require AI to be better than humans in any global sense. It's enough for AI to be good enough, cheap, fast, and deployable at scale, which she calls in the talk and elsewhere 'Artificial Good-Enough Intelligence.'","source_id":"src-839b9146139a","date":"2025-12-01","confidence":"high","x":-0.2827533629574698,"y":8.710060762255345,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Ill-defined","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":989,"name":"E. Glen Weyl","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"Superintelligence already exists in collective systems humanity has created—markets, democracies, corporations, religious communities","citation":"Glen Weyl, researcher and economist at Microsoft and co-founder of the Plurality Institute, does not think superintelligence is something we are waiting to build. He argues that it already exists—in the collective systems humanity has created, from markets and democracies to corporations and religious communities.","source_id":"src-36f89aad98f9","date":"2025-12-01","confidence":"high","x":0.1967491781289664,"y":4.084693259451283,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":990,"name":"Gary Marcus","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is a shorthand for any intelligence that is flexible and general, with resourcefulness and reliability comparable to (or beyond) human intelligence","citation":"I take AGI to be \"a shorthand for any intelligence ... that is flexible and general, with resourcefulness and reliability comparable to (or beyond) human intelligence\".","source_id":"src-34e986a5c6a5","date":"2025-01-07","confidence":"high","x":0.9498080660936946,"y":7.7650732159266855,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":991,"name":"Noam Chomsky","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"Chomsky does not use the term AGI directly; he frames the question of machines surpassing humans in terms of performance (capacity to act) vs. competence (internal cognitive structures), arguing that engineering projects can surpass human performance but cannot replicate human linguistic competence or understanding.","citation":"It is quite possible that future engineering projects will match and even surpass human capabilities, if we mean human capacity to act, performance. As mentioned above, some have long done so: automatic calculators for example. More interestingly, as mentioned, insects with minuscule brains surpass human capacities understood as competence.","source_id":"src-2129c39100b7","date":"2023-05-02","confidence":"medium","x":0.278337545658008,"y":7.462673237122257,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"Ill-defined","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":992,"name":"Alison Gopnik","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"Intelligence is not a single capacity but a collection of distinct cognitive modes: exploration (learning about the world), exploitation (acting effectively toward goals), and care (helping other agents achieve their goals).","citation":"Gopnik identifies three distinct types of intelligence: exploration (learning about the world), exploitation (acting effectively toward goals), and care (helping other agents achieve their goals).","source_id":"src-e2ded3814b3b","date":"2026-04-17","confidence":"high","x":0.3139328252224514,"y":3.5928514443908544,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"25+ years or never","timeline_score":5,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":993,"name":"Divya Siddarth","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"Prefers moving from artificial general intelligence to augmented collective intelligence, where AI amplifies rather than replaces human agency.","citation":"A better tech future moves from artificial general intelligence to augmented collective intelligence, where AI amplifies rather than replaces human agency.","source_id":"src-3ed321059996","date":"2025-09-29","confidence":"medium","x":-0.6408878614311304,"y":3.7174751026549693,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"augmentative-tools","cluster_label":"Augmentative Tools"},{"entity_id":995,"name":"Saffron Huang","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is a theoretical advanced technology intended to surpass human cognitive abilities, which may one day put most people out of work; only the world's wealthiest tech companies are currently battling to build it.","citation":"Only the world's wealthiest tech companies–or startups partnered with them–are battling it out to build artificial general intelligence, a theoretical advanced technology intended to surpass human cognitive abilities, which may one day put most people out of work.","source_id":"src-5b2915371ab1","date":"2024-09-05","confidence":"medium","x":0.44777785245304913,"y":9.002271758264879,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":999,"name":"Nate Soares","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AI that exceeds humans at all cognitive tasks","citation":"If at any point there is an AI that exceeds humans at all cognitive tasks... not in the AI companies redefine super intelligence to mean a slightly better Google search, but if at some point there is an AI that exceeds humans at all cognitive tasks.","source_id":"src-8bfd51803cb2","date":"2025-09-30","confidence":"high","x":1.524757393711827,"y":2.5958632719765986,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":1000,"name":"Sundar Pichai","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"Current AI phase characterized by dramatic progress alongside basic failures, where models can perform impressive tasks but make simple errors like counting","citation":"\"But if your question is will it happen by 2030? Look, we constantly move the line of what it means to be AGI... I almost feel the term doesn't matter, what I know is by 2030 there'll be such dramatic progress.\"","source_id":"src-835a58822d1c","date":"2025-06-04","confidence":"high","x":0.17916898476177456,"y":3.4016642580863232,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1001,"name":"Satya Nadella","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"Nadella defines AI using Raj Reddy's metaphor as either a 'guardian angel' or a 'cognitive amplifier' - focusing on human utility rather than general intelligence.","citation":"He had this metaphor for AI, it should either be a guardian angel or a cognitive amplifier. I love that. It's a simple way to think about what this is.","source_id":"src-cd50a8dfe028","date":"2025-11-12","confidence":"high","x":-0.7596351872709021,"y":3.566907974929865,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"augmentative-tools","cluster_label":"Augmentative Tools"},{"entity_id":1002,"name":"Tristan Harris","entity_type":"person","category":"Organizer","definition":"AGI is AI that can replace all forms of human economic and cognitive labor - everything a person can do with their brain including marketing, writing, illustration, video production, and coding","citation":"Their mission is to be able to replace all forms of human economic labor in the economy, meaning an AI that can do all the cognitive labor, meaning labor of the mind, so that that can be marketing, that can be text, that can be illustration, that can be video production, that can be code production, everything that a person can do with their brain.","source_id":"src-bb4342e3c010","date":"2025-11-01","confidence":"high","x":0.8884701342603427,"y":8.948121632865533,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":1003,"name":"Aza Raskin","entity_type":"person","category":"Organizer","definition":"The ability for an AI to replace human beings behind a screen - if the economy can't tell that we swapped out a human with an AI, that's what AGI is.","citation":"You can still broadly understand AGI as the ability for an AI to replace human beings behind a screen. That is, if the economy can't tell that we swapped out a human with an AI, well, that's what AGI is.","source_id":"src-7e4df0001a8a","date":"2025-04-29","confidence":"high","x":-1.2672779452372391,"y":7.940953309032037,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":1006,"name":"Marco Rubio","entity_type":"person","category":"Policymaker","definition":"AI is simply the automated statistical analysis of data that uses what happened yesterday to predict what will happen today or tomorrow","citation":"First, we know what AI is. It's not an alien consciousness, nor is it a magic eight-ball with the solution to every world problem at its fingertips. AI is simply the automated statistical analysis of data. Think of it as a computer program that uses what happened yesterday to predict what will happen today or tomorrow.","source_id":"src-e27c53596d93","date":"2023-07-16","confidence":"high","x":-1.1431765558533138,"y":3.77557286295759,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Mixed/nuanced","risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1007,"name":"Andrej Karpathy","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is a system that can do any economically valuable task at human performance or better, including physical tasks, though Karpathy acknowledges current discourse often narrows this to knowledge work only.","citation":"\"When people talk about AI and the original AGI and how we spoke about it when OpenAI started, AGI was a system you could go to that can do any economically valuable task at human performance or better. That was the definition. I was pretty happy with that at the time. I've stuck to that definition forever, and then people have made up all kinds of other definitions. But I like that definition.\"","source_id":"src-728009cd946b","date":"2025-10-16","confidence":"high","x":-0.7873890903043662,"y":7.41359157754977,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":1009,"name":"Bill Gates","entity_type":"person","category":"Investor","definition":"AGI refers to software that's capable of learning any task or subject, contrasting with current AI that solves specific problems or provides particular services.","citation":"By contrast, the term artificial general intelligence refers to software that's capable of learning any task or subject. AGI doesn't exist yet—there is a robust debate going on in the computing industry about how to create it, and whether it can even be created at all.","source_id":"src-31dc038a19b4","date":"2023-03-21","confidence":"high","x":1.1058878420452005,"y":7.504565374512139,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":1011,"name":"Naval Ravikant","entity_type":"person","category":"Investor","definition":"AGI can do anything and has unpredictable thinking that produces ideas nobody predicted, unlike AI which can only do narrow specified tasks.","citation":"Naval Ravikant: \"Related to that, we've touched upon AGI [artificial general intelligence] here and there. You have said AGI is absolutely possible, and that Turing settled that issue. Now some people are saying it's almost inevitable and we have to worry about things like AGI alignment. I'm wondering if you have thoughts on both, is self-improving, runaway AGI here?\"","source_id":"src-e01857f7a24b","date":"2023-03-24","confidence":"medium","x":0.7407817288933873,"y":7.420777239144653,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":1015,"name":"Kevin Kelly","entity_type":"person","category":"Cultural figure","definition":"Kelly defines intelligence as having three modes: Knowledge reasoning (LLM-type), World sense (spatial/physical intelligence), and Continuous learning - with current AI only having the first","citation":"I propose three general classes of cognition that together can make something like a human intelligence. The three modes are: 1) Knowledge reasoning, 2) World sense, and 3) Continuous memory and learning.","source_id":"src-e5a178f113a7","date":"2026-03-02","confidence":"high","x":0.4486731630673458,"y":3.482487155282847,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1109,"name":"Berkeley Artificial Intelligence Research","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI as machines that match or exceed human capabilities in every relevant dimension, capable of general-purpose intelligent behavior.","citation":"The long-standing goal of AI has been to create general-purpose AI systems—also known as artificial general intelligence or AGI—that match or exceed human capabilities in every relevant dimension.","source_id":"src-49e24bb9a0a2","date":"2023-11-29","confidence":"high","x":0.4338796576942093,"y":7.394455389237023,"stance":null,"stance_score":null,"timeline":null,"timeline_score":null,"risk":null,"risk_score":null,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1123,"name":"Marc Benioff","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AI can perform complex, human-level tasks","citation":"\"But it's not a person, and it's not intelligent, and it's not conscious,\" Benioff said. \"It hasn't suffered, it doesn't have compassion.\"","source_id":"src-551e575a1b5f","date":"2025-07-31","confidence":"medium","x":1.7579302738306466,"y":2.7495597567513514,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1141,"name":"Neil Lawrence","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"Lawrence rejects the concept of artificial general intelligence as fundamentally flawed, comparing it to an 'artificial general vehicle' - a vehicle that would be optimal in all situations, which he calls absurd.","citation":"\"There are general principles underlying intelligence, but the notion of a rankable form of intelligence where one entity dominates all others is fundamentally flawed. Yet it is this notion that underpins the modern idea of artificial general intelligence.\"","source_id":"src-b3c268691b4d","date":"2026-02-05","confidence":"high","x":1.660003408327935,"y":5.1997328386196555,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1145,"name":"Kyunghyun Cho","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is treated skeptically as a term — Cho describes it as a 'magic wand' used to mesmerize the public and distract from critical analysis of current AI impacts, rather than a well-defined technical concept.","citation":"But at the moment, AGI is kind of a magic wand that they are just trying to swing to mesmerize people so that people fail to be critical about what is going on.","source_id":"src-17ebea22d328","date":"2023-05-31","confidence":"high","x":-0.755992224649304,"y":9.37722482208686,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1148,"name":"Senate Committee on Commerce, Science and Transportation","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"AGI is a system that can tackle increasingly complex problems, at human level, in many fields — as stated by witness Sam Altman in testimony before the committee.","citation":"\"Our mission is to ensure that artificial general intelligence – AGI – benefits all of humanity. AGI is a weakly defined term, but generally speaking we mean it to be a system that can tackle increasingly complex problems, at human level, in many fields.\"","source_id":"src-4db658873f61","date":"2025-05-07","confidence":"high","x":-0.12741857446962396,"y":7.099166998574709,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1169,"name":"Trump administration","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"A system capable of doing almost any cognitive task a human can do, with systems that can replace human beings in cognitively demanding jobs","citation":"A canonical definition of A.G.I. is a system capable of doing almost any cognitive task a human can do. I don't know that we'll quite see that in the next four years or so, but I do think we'll see something like that, where the breadth of the system is remarkable but also its depth, its capacity to, in some cases, exceed human capabilities, regardless of the cognitive discipline — Systems that can replace human beings in cognitively demanding jobs.","source_id":"src-f5ff4289bd59","date":"2025-03-05","confidence":"medium","x":1.0576851850870848,"y":2.886754016480822,"stance":"Accelerate","stance_score":1,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":1192,"name":"IBM","entity_type":"organization","category":"Deployers & Platforms","definition":"IBM defines AGI as a hypothetical stage where an artificial intelligence system can match or exceed the cognitive abilities of human beings across any task","citation":"IBM gives one of the more succinct and straightforward definitions of AGI: 'Artificial general intelligence is a hypothetical stage in the development of machine learning in which an artificial intelligence system can match or exceed the cognitive abilities of human beings across any task'.","source_id":"src-488804d649e0","date":"2025-05-16","confidence":"high","x":0.2902752617368702,"y":8.329848101581602,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1196,"name":"Brad Smith","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AGI is where computers are more powerful than people (i.e., super-intelligent AI surpassing human capabilities).","citation":"\"There's absolutely no probability that you're going to see this so-called AGI, where computers are more powerful than people, in the next 12 months.\"","source_id":"src-283ab1584667","date":"2023-11-30","confidence":"high","x":0.8435907822636373,"y":8.205749371000225,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":1201,"name":"Danielle Li","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI emphasizes broad reasoning and problem-solving capabilities","citation":"While definitions of artificial general intelligence (AGI) emphasize broad reasoning and problem-solving capabilities (Bubeck et al., 2023), even highly capable models would still require context-specific training and examples to excel at actual workplace tasks (Mitchell, 2021).","source_id":"src-3a71a7f87cbd","date":"2025-01-31","confidence":"high","x":1.2055529038636668,"y":9.00126284049476,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":1203,"name":"Casey Mock","entity_type":"person","category":"Organizer","definition":"Human intelligence isn't just computational power plus data, but it involves embodied experience, cultural context, and neurosymbolic understanding that current AI systems fundamentally lack.","citation":"In my opinion, the fundamental misunderstanding across these groups is a reductive view of intelligence itself. Human intelligence isn't just computational power plus data, but it involves embodied experience, cultural context, and neurosymbolic understanding that current AI systems fundamentally lack.","source_id":"src-74c3d499d776","date":"2025-05-20","confidence":"high","x":0.015564723003193955,"y":3.5430525947970346,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1225,"name":"Alphabet Inc.","entity_type":"organization","category":"Deployers & Platforms","definition":"Systems with fundamental human-like capabilities including continual learning, long-term planning, and consistency, addressing current 'jagged intelligence' limitations.","citation":"Current AI systems, as Google DeepMind's Demis Hassabis describes them, are still 'jagged intelligences.' The core problem is a lack of fundamental human-like capabilities: they cannot learn continuously after deployment, struggle with long-term planning, and lack the consistency needed for real-world reliability.","source_id":"src-9e57c7aa714b","date":"2026-02-19","confidence":"high","x":0.8698690851122302,"y":3.267933927234726,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":1241,"name":"U.S. Army","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"AGI seeks to provide machines with comparable human intelligence, able to perform any intellectual task that humans can.","citation":"There is also a subset of AI known as Artificial General Intelligence (AGI), which has been slow in development as it seeks to provide machines with comparable human intelligence, able to perform any intellectual task that humans can.","source_id":"src-e22e0f6bd189","date":"2025-07-02","confidence":"high","x":0.6264568950628031,"y":8.129070423044427,"stance":"Accelerate","stance_score":1,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1260,"name":"UNESCO","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"Strong AI or AGI would be a machine that has consciousness and feelings, and is capable of providing solutions for any kind of problem","citation":"Strong AI or AGI would be a machine that has consciousness and feelings, and is capable of providing solutions for any kind of problem – that is pure fiction, for now.","source_id":"src-ca294f36fe05","date":"2023-05-10","confidence":"high","x":0.2671798969999205,"y":8.057252688583267,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1262,"name":"European Artificial Intelligence Board","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"AI capable of performing any cognitive task that humans can","citation":"Current advances in memory, reasoning, and autonomous behaviour are paving the way towards Artificial General Intelligence (AGI), understood as AI capable of performing any cognitive task that humans can.","source_id":"src-7c787a22152d","date":"2025-10-07","confidence":"high","x":1.5252680801195768,"y":2.616167741209293,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1287,"name":"Kartik Hosanagar","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI should not be LLMs overloaded as monolithic systems, but rather LLMs acting as language processors that interface with other computational systems to generate reliable results.","citation":"There's a fundamental issue with how LLMs are marketed and consumed. They're often pitched as AGI, and while their mastery of language is impressive, this framing is misleading and can be damaging. Our brains have multiple specialized centers each of which perform different functions: the frontal lobe, temporal lobe, limbic system, etc. But LLMs are being overloaded as monolithic AGI system—one that undeniably excels at language but thrust with responsibilities far beyond their capabilities.","source_id":"src-70cce379d4ac","date":"2025-03-04","confidence":"high","x":-0.7259420906816009,"y":6.721911633202674,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1295,"name":"Office of Management and Budget","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"OMB uses the statutory definition from the McCain NDAA which includes artificial systems that perform tasks under varying circumstances, solve tasks requiring human-like cognition, or are designed to think or act like humans","citation":"The term 'artificial intelligence' includes the following: 1. Any artificial system that performs tasks under varying and unpredictable circumstances without significant human oversight, or that can learn from experience and improve performance when exposed to data sets. 2. An artificial system developed in computer software, physical hardware, or other context that solves tasks requiring human-like perception, cognition, planning, learning, communication, or physical action. 3. An artificial system designed to think or act like a human, including cognitive architectures and neural networks.","source_id":"src-d6390c63d525","date":"2024-03-28","confidence":"high","x":0.5407135392020455,"y":2.961577423802759,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1297,"name":"Sebastian Thrun","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI capability measured by comparing what AI can do versus what normal people (not Einsteins) are asked to do - such as high school or college-level tasks like passing the bar exam.","citation":"\"auf einem Sektor ein nach einer Dimension haben wir es bereits erreicht und an der anderen werden wir es lange nicht erreichen... AI schafft das bereits 99,99%... Was es nicht schafft, sind diese out of the box moments, wo es keine Repetition mehr gibt, wo was Neues und neuer Gedanke erfunden muss.\"","source_id":"src-5e8c92a3bf32","date":"2025-07-09","confidence":"high","x":-0.35732676442109806,"y":8.572288028436976,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1309,"name":"National Institute of Standards and Technology","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"AI agents capable of autonomous actions that function securely on behalf of users and interoperate across digital systems","citation":"The AI Agent Standards Initiative ensures that the next generation of AI—agents capable of autonomous actions—is widely adopted with confidence. By fostering industry-led technical standards and open protocols, NIST aims to catalyze an ecosystem where agents function securely on behalf of users and interoperate smoothly across the digital landscape while cementing U.S. dominance at the technological frontier.","source_id":"src-8d8b1f98952f","date":"2026-02-17","confidence":"medium","x":-0.5572666310145339,"y":5.157816410941213,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":1310,"name":"Ylli Bajraktari","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AGI is defined as a staged progression through four levels: current AI, a 'more-general' intermediate stage, AGI that disrupts whole economic verticals, and artificial superintelligence (ASI) that exceeds human capabilities in some domains.","citation":"The resulting path to AGI will proceed in four simple stages of 1) AI of today, 2) some intermediate stage that is 'more-general' as discussed by the NSCAI, 3) AGI that begins to disrupt (positively and negatively) whole verticals of the economy, and 4) something better than humans in some aspects called artificial super-intelligence (ASI).","source_id":"src-33c883084386","date":"2024-09-10","confidence":"high","x":-0.5558662370434373,"y":7.340210727176625,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":1321,"name":"ServiceNow","entity_type":"organization","category":"Deployers & Platforms","definition":"Artificial general intelligence is an AI agent that is fully capable of the advanced problem solving, critical thinking, and cognitive function of a human being.","citation":"Artificial general intelligence is an AI agent that is fully capable of the advanced problem solving, critical thinking, and cognitive function of a human being. This is currently a hypothetical branch of artificial intelligence that researchers and businesses are actively working to develop.","source_id":"src-10c6ad0c7ad1","date":"2024-05-04","confidence":"high","x":1.540074081667625,"y":5.816349213710623,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1322,"name":"Government of Canada","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"General AI systems that can perform any cognitive task as well as or better than a human are outside the scope of current strategy, focusing instead on narrow AI for specific tasks","citation":"Even the most advanced AI today is narrow AI: tools focused on specific tasks such as pattern recognition, classification, task optimization, and anomaly detection. Experts disagree on when or even if general AI, which can perform any cognitive task as well as or better than a human, will ever be developed. General AI systems are therefore outside the scope of this Strategy.","source_id":"src-6c646acd64b0","date":"2024-03-21","confidence":"high","x":1.5699666264849306,"y":4.3389701030978465,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1325,"name":"Amnesty International","entity_type":"organization","category":"Ethics/Bias/Rights","definition":"There is no widespread consensus on the definition of AI because the term does not refer to a singular technology and rather encapsulates a myriad technological applications and methods.","citation":"There is no widespread consensus on the definition of AI because the term does not refer to a singular technology and rather encapsulates a myriad technological applications and methods.","source_id":"src-d8bd6c151d0b","date":"2024-01-16","confidence":"medium","x":-1.4267502900058633,"y":3.777776148494,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1329,"name":"Apple","entity_type":"organization","category":"Deployers & Platforms","definition":"Apple views AGI as requiring many unsolved problems and breakthroughs, rejecting the idea that current scaling approaches will achieve it","citation":"The most credible researchers in the field believe there are many unsolved problems and breakthroughs required. The idea that you're scaling up these technologies to go to AGI is very naive.","source_id":"src-4e2c2a7bd0b8","date":"2024-12-09","confidence":"high","x":-0.4867074329751491,"y":8.940674125633713,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":null,"timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1336,"name":"OECD","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"Artificial general intelligence (AGI) is generally understood as AI that matches the full range of human cognitive and social abilities.","citation":"The OECD AI Capability Indicators offer a potential framework for defining and measuring artificial general intelligence (AGI), which is generally understood as AI that matches the full range of human cognitive and social abilities.","source_id":"src-7eaf51180e16","date":"2025-05-27","confidence":"high","x":1.5051824576074062,"y":6.778839513151269,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1349,"name":"Ben Mann","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"Mann prefers 'transformative AI' over AGI, defining it through an economic Turing test where if you contract an agent for a month and decide to hire it without knowing it's a machine, it passes the test for that role.","citation":"I think AGI is a loaded term, and so I tend not to use it very much anymore internally. Instead, I like the term transformative AI, because it's less about can it do as much as people do, can it do literally everything, and more about objectively is it causing transformation in society and the economy? A very concrete way of measuring that is the economic Turing test.","source_id":"src-07464c94126e","date":"2025-07-24","confidence":"high","x":-1.3653428293715808,"y":7.88747281445836,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":1351,"name":"Eleos AI","entity_type":"organization","category":"AI Safety/Alignment","definition":"Eleos refers to 'transformative artificial intelligence (TAI)' and 'general intelligence' as overlapping capabilities, focusing on consciousness and robust agency rather than providing a specific AGI definition.","citation":"As part of the overall project of navigating the development of advanced AI, we see the potential moral status of AI systems themselves as an important and neglected issue... as we navigate transformative artificial intelligence (TAI).","source_id":"src-5052f6e06ac8","date":"2024-06-30","confidence":"medium","x":-1.8808934954752938,"y":7.645215930989739,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1352,"name":"David Chalmers","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI involves sophisticated general abilities across multiple domains, potentially including consciousness and subjective experience, not just cognitive task performance.","citation":"Among people who think about consciousness, domain-general use of information is often regarded as one of the central signs of consciousness. So the fact that we are seeing increasing generality in these language models may suggest a move in the direction of consciousness.","source_id":"src-0fbb3cf1c6b7","date":"2023-06-30","confidence":"high","x":0.18074556862523622,"y":7.8865968137286915,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Ill-defined","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1356,"name":"Niskanen Center","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AGI refers to systems that match human cognitive capabilities - basically anything human beings can do on a computer, Claude would be as good or better than the best people in the world","citation":"The head of Anthropic, Dario Amodei, talks about a country of geniuses in a data center – that this is powerful AI or superhuman AI or AGI or whatever. So, we're talking about some qualitative improvement over where we are now, such that basically anything human beings can do on a computer, Claude would be as good or better than the best people in the world.","source_id":"src-62ed5e9285cb","date":"2026-04-22","confidence":"medium","x":0.5021696642006647,"y":8.324076190974164,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1357,"name":"Federation of American Scientists","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"AGI refers to a human-like ability to pursue long-term goals and exercise purposive behavior, seeking general cognitive abilities rather than being oriented around specific tasks.","citation":"The JASON report distinguishes between artificial intelligence — referring to the ability of computers to perform particular tasks that humans do with their brains — and artificial general intelligence (AGI) — meaning a human-like ability to pursue long-term goals and exercise purposive behavior. 'Where AI is oriented around specific tasks, AGI seeks general cognitive abilities.'","source_id":"src-b1a157250d3f","date":"2017-01-11","confidence":"high","x":-0.06326875812182908,"y":7.703086944508169,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":null,"timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":1358,"name":"U.S. Artificial Intelligence Safety Institute","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"Advanced AI systems, models, and agents with capabilities that can perform tasks once thought to require human-level intelligence, including frontier AI models requiring scientific evaluation for safety","citation":"This calls for institutions that conduct scientific research, articulate practices and protocols, and convene communities to promote safe AI models and systems... A lack of commonly accepted definitions for AI safety, as well as AI safety capabilities and measurements of those capabilities, especially for frontier models and advanced AI agents and systems.","source_id":"src-0017a9e19e40","date":"2024-05-20","confidence":"medium","x":0.7231334870597191,"y":5.533012505577834,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1360,"name":"UK government's Frontier AI Taskforce","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"A theoretical form of advanced AI that would have capabilities that compare to or exceed humans across most economically valuable work.","citation":"Artificial General Intelligence (AGI): A theoretical form of advanced AI that would have capabilities that compare to or exceed humans across most economically valuable work.","source_id":"src-aef604e25310","date":"2024-02-05","confidence":"high","x":-0.005258982143139149,"y":2.079747294671067,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":null,"timeline_score":null,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":1362,"name":"MIT Computer Science & Artificial Intelligence Laboratory","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"A level of machine intelligence that surpasses the current state of the art in AI, going beyond statistics, data processing and pattern recognition toward deep reasoning, real-world understanding, and autonomous problem solving across disciplines","citation":"The broad goal of U.S. AI policy should be to drive toward what we call Artificial Super Intelligence – a level of machine intelligence that surpasses the current state of the art in AI, going beyond statistics, data processing and pattern recognition toward deep reasoning, real-world understanding, and autonomous problem solving across disciplines.","source_id":"src-c7b938501028","date":"2025-04-09","confidence":"high","x":0.5888286252572299,"y":4.107129225732765,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":1364,"name":"Shane Legg","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"Minimal AGI is an artificial agent that can perform all the kinds of cognitive tasks that typical humans can do, setting the bar at typical human performance to avoid being too low or too high.","citation":"So my my definition of AGI or sometimes called minimal AGI is it's an artificial agent that can at least do the kinds of cognitive things people can typically do.","source_id":"src-c7ee66bef7f3","date":"2025-12-11","confidence":"high","x":-0.504881182257515,"y":8.211054788598313,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1365,"name":"Mustafa Suleyman","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"A general-purpose learning system that can perform well across all human-level training environments, including knowledge work and physical labor, without extensive handcrafted prompting.","citation":"To me, AGI is a general-purpose learning system that can perform well across all human-level training environments. So, knowledge work, by the way, that includes physical labor.","source_id":"src-80a095d97fd4","date":"2024-12-09","confidence":"high","x":1.5090443409131382,"y":3.367820924150554,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":1368,"name":"Margaret Mitchell","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is an ambiguous concept lacking agreed-upon definitions for both 'intelligence' and 'general'; Mitchell calls it 'just vibes and snake oil' and argues it should not serve as a guiding principle for the AI industry.","citation":"Margaret Mitchell, chief ethics scientist at Hugging Face and founder of Google's responsible AI team, has dismissed artificial general intelligence as \"just vibes and snake oil.\" Mitchell... contends that both \"intelligence\" and \"general\" lack clear definitions in AI contexts, creating what she calls an…","source_id":"src-8a447bd30563","date":"2025-06-18","confidence":"high","x":-0.4456233964391375,"y":9.192247907413602,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1383,"name":"Stanford Vision and Learning Lab","entity_type":"organization","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI represents a significant leap in the capability of machines to perform tasks that require human-level intelligence, such as reasoning, problem-solving, decision-making, and even understanding human emotions and social interactions.","citation":"AGI, driven by the recent large pre-trained models, represents a significant leap in the capability of machines to perform tasks that require human-level intelligence, such as reasoning, problem-solving, decision-making, and even understanding human emotions and social interactions.","source_id":"src-774a1dd06f25","date":"2024-03-01","confidence":"medium","x":0.6061107931371934,"y":8.306347961006963,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1393,"name":"Scott Alexander","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is human-level AI (artificial general intelligence).","citation":"Planning For AGI And Beyond (\"AGI\" = \"artificial general intelligence\", ie human-level AI) is the latest volley in that campaign.","source_id":"src-1f4d56ec9c98","date":"2023-03-01","confidence":"high","x":1.5664469967881187,"y":7.901480779829003,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1394,"name":"Thomas Larsen","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is an AI system capable of autonomous, catastrophe-capable actions — particularly autonomous AI capabilities performing dangerous tasks mostly without humans in the loop, including potential recursive self-improvement and self-exfiltration.","citation":"What I'm most worried about is autonomous AI capabilities doing dangerous tasks, mostly without humans in the loop... have the labs commit to stop scaling once we get sufficiently capable models, right? Like, let's say we get models that are sufficiently capable that they can self-exfiltrate from the labs, given our security measures.","source_id":"src-67877511c58b","date":"2024-05-21","confidence":"medium","x":0.015724349879455913,"y":7.221870525321025,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":1408,"name":"Senate AI Caucus","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"AGI is recognized as having significant uncertainty and no widespread agreement on definition or achievement threshold","citation":"The AI Working Group recognizes that there is not widespread agreement on the definition of AGI or threshold by which it will officially be achieved. Therefore, we encourage the relevant committees to better define AGI in consultation with experts, characterize both the likelihood of AGI development and the magnitude of the risks that AGI development would pose, and develop an appropriate policy framework based on that analysis.","source_id":"src-588ff36b9290","date":"2024-05-13","confidence":"high","x":-1.6325418199822281,"y":9.076246841949196,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1412,"name":"Roger Wicker","entity_type":"person","category":"Policymaker","definition":"Scientists create artificial intelligence by using math to teach computers how to solve problems and recognize patterns","citation":"We call this intelligence \"artificial\" because scientists create it. They use math to teach computers how to solve problems and recognize patterns.","source_id":"src-b6d8a043df08","date":"2025-05-18","confidence":"medium","x":0.6296821004849442,"y":3.9766891572055916,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1417,"name":"Department of Energy","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"A machine-based system that can, for a given set of human-defined objectives, make predictions, recommendations, or decisions influencing real or virtual environments using machine- and human-based inputs to perceive environments and formulate options through automated analysis and model inference.","citation":"The field of artificial intelligence (AI) has a long intellectual history, with a broad variety of models and approaches developed over time. EO 14110 and United States Code defines Artificial Intelligence as: …a machine-based system that can, for a given set of human-defined objectives, make predictions, recommendations, or decisions influencing real or virtual environments.","source_id":"src-409dd9081071","date":"2024-04-29","confidence":"high","x":-1.0404638966057873,"y":4.227076077318143,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":null,"timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":1420,"name":"Department of Defense","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"Artificial general intelligence refers to a theoretical form of AI that would be capable of human-level cognition","citation":"AGI refers to a theoretical form of AI that would be capable of human-level cognition.","source_id":"src-9ad47f1d9e95","date":"2026-01-14","confidence":"medium","x":1.6770342429960554,"y":5.551688624368401,"stance":"Accelerate","stance_score":1,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1424,"name":"Shelley Moore Capito","entity_type":"person","category":"Policymaker","definition":"Machines that are capable of intelligence or decision-making actions similar to humans.","citation":"AI has been in the news for much of the year. It can be generally defined as machines that are capable of intelligence or decision-making actions similar to humans.","source_id":"src-77cb7326b286","date":"2023-11-01","confidence":"medium","x":0.19321913918867198,"y":3.236189473312464,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1427,"name":"Senate Committee on Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"The AI Working Group recognizes that there is not widespread agreement on the definition of AGI or threshold by which it will officially be achieved.","citation":"The AI Working Group recognizes that there is not widespread agreement on the definition of AGI or threshold by which it will officially be achieved. Therefore, we encourage the relevant committees to better define AGI in consultation with experts, characterize both the likelihood of AGI development and the magnitude of the risks that AGI development would pose, and develop an appropriate policy framework based on that analysis.","source_id":"src-588ff36b9290","date":"2024-05-13","confidence":"high","x":-1.8484533505213856,"y":8.903042168647692,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1428,"name":"U.S. Senate Commerce Committee","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"AGI definition is uncertain and contested; the Senate AI Working Group recognized there is 'not widespread agreement on the definition of AGI or threshold by which it will officially be achieved' and called on relevant committees (including Commerce) to better define it in consultation with experts.","citation":"\"Recognizes the significant level of uncertainty and unknowns associated with general purpose AI systems achieving AGI. At the same time, the AI Working Group recognizes that there is not widespread agreement on the definition of AGI or threshold by which it will officially be achieved. Therefore, we encourage the relevant committees to better define AGI in consultation with experts.\"","source_id":"src-c1e776c5f0d6","date":"2024-04-30","confidence":"high","x":-1.848488462679578,"y":8.942133736767689,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1437,"name":"National Artificial Intelligence Advisory Commission","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"AGI is referenced in NAIAC's statutory mandate as a benchmark for tracking the 'state of the science around artificial intelligence, including progress toward artificial general intelligence,' without providing a specific technical definition.","citation":"the state of the science around artificial intelligence, including progress toward artificial general intelligence;","source_id":"src-9444731ce18c","date":"2020-12-20","confidence":"medium","x":-0.30924540970391645,"y":8.460681474207453,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1438,"name":"U.S. Department of Labor","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"AI is a machine-based system that can, for a given set of human-defined objectives, make predictions, recommendations, or decisions influencing real or virtual environments using machine- and human-based inputs to perceive environments and formulate options for action.","citation":"As set forth in 15 U.S.C. § 9401(3), AI is a machine-based system that can, for a given set of human-defined objectives, make predictions, recommendations, or decisions influencing real or virtual environments. AI systems use machine- and human-based inputs to perceive real and virtual environments; abstract such perceptions into models through analysis in an automated manner; and use model inference to formulate options for information or action.","source_id":"src-8836b9853f17","date":"2025-01-13","confidence":"high","x":-1.0421191368350118,"y":4.205305106183817,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":1451,"name":"John Tasioulas","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"Intelligence that replicates the entire spectrum of human intelligence, able to write a poem, make a cancer diagnosis, make a hiring decision, do everything that a human can do","citation":"All the big tech corporations say they have the same goal. Their goal is to create artificial general intelligence. Artificial general intelligence is intelligence that is replicating the entire spectrum of human intelligence. So able to write a poem, make a cancer diagnosis, make a hiring decision, do everything that a human can do.","source_id":"src-be0f8d92b47e","date":"2024-01-01","confidence":"high","x":0.2111680994088336,"y":2.8627838374442165,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1489,"name":"Rodney Brooks","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"Brooks views AGI as part of a continuum of AI development that has been the goal all along, rejecting the term as a recent marketing construct.","citation":"\"What I hate now is artificial general intelligence. We were always working toward artificial general intelligence!\" he said, \"and soon they'll be calling it artificial superintelligence.\"","source_id":"src-c2b74f2afd12","date":"2026-01-08","confidence":"high","x":-1.010365695430136,"y":8.721856678375191,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"25+ years or never","timeline_score":5,"risk":"Overstated","risk_score":1,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1491,"name":"ACM US Technology Policy Committee","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"A machine-based system that can, for a given set of human-defined objectives, make predictions, recommendations or decisions influencing real or virtual environments through perceiving environments, abstracting perceptions into models, and using model inference to formulate options.","citation":"The term ''artificial intelligence'' means a machine-based system that can, for a given set of human-defined objectives, make predictions, recommendations or decisions influencing real or virtual environments. Artificial intelligence systems use machine and human-based inputs to (A) perceive real and virtual environments; (B) abstract such perceptions into models through analysis in an automated manner; and (C) use model inference to formulate options for information or action.","source_id":"src-2ae2cdf7193b","date":"2025-03-14","confidence":"high","x":-1.0752841651828144,"y":4.276624989883156,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":1496,"name":"Mark Muro","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is referenced implicitly as an advanced AI capable of significant employment disruption on a 'short timeline,' without Muro providing a formal personal definition; he uses the term in the context of AI systems that would displace workers across many industries.","citation":"Roose sharpens the moment by noting that most folks he talks to in the Bay Area AI community now have the arrival of what's called 'artificial general intelligence' (AGI) on a 'short timeline.'","source_id":"src-88e2c662c370","date":"2025-03-17","confidence":"low","x":0.3336356532303334,"y":8.942256229097868,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":1507,"name":"Buck Shlegeris","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AI systems capable of automating almost all the work that human researchers do inside AI companies, running in parallel at speeds far exceeding humans, with the ability to cause catastrophic harm if misaligned — situated in an 'intermediate zone' between current AI and drastically superhuman superintelligence.","citation":"I mostly think about situations where, in the middle of the intelligence explosion, you have AIs that are basically capable of automating almost all the work that human researchers used to be doing inside AI companies. You have maybe 100,000 of them running in parallel, and they each run like 15 times faster than a human.","source_id":"src-080a9293f490","date":"2025-04-03","confidence":"medium","x":-0.2487776119209076,"y":2.9449853464881204,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"autonomous-research-capability","cluster_label":"Autonomous Research"},{"entity_id":1510,"name":"Ryan Greenblatt","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AI able to do everything needed to run an AI company, from writing code to designing experiments to making strategic and business decisions","citation":"Ryan Greenblatt — lead author on the explosive paper \"Alignment faking in large language models\" and chief scientist at Redwood Research— thinks there's a 25% chance that within four years, AI will be able to do everything needed to run an AI company, from writing code to designing experiments to making strategic and business decisions.","source_id":"src-68f7acc52194","date":"2025-07-07","confidence":"high","x":0.03809751068157471,"y":2.897208370455492,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"autonomous-research-capability","cluster_label":"Autonomous Research"},{"entity_id":1526,"name":"Tom Brown","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"Weak AGI already exists in conversational AI systems, with stronger versions emerging as models get smarter and gain more 'IQ points' through increased compute","citation":"I think we already have weak AGI. You can talk with ChatGPT or Claude and it's somewhat intelligent, and with each year it's improving. Right now you may prompt the model to build a successful startup. It'll try to do it, but it'll get stuck. But as we add more compute, the model gets smarter.","source_id":"src-9a8fc36b307a","date":"2023-12-19","confidence":"high","x":1.5980176272552207,"y":8.32538994748937,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1531,"name":"Zoë Hitzig","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"Hitzig does not offer her own definition of AGI but questions the sincerity and coherence of OpenAI's stated mission to 'ensure that artificial general intelligence benefits all of humanity,' expressing skepticism about what builders of these tools actually envision for humanity.","citation":"\"OpenAI's mission is 'to ensure that artificial general intelligence benefits all of humanity', but I'm not sure what their vision of humanity really is. When you hear Sam Altman comparing the energy consumption required to train a human mind to the energy consumption required to train an artificial mind… Is that really how you think of us, as inefficient consumers of resources?\"","source_id":"src-9c99cfd6ec14","date":"2026-03-27","confidence":"medium","x":-0.9541611363065227,"y":7.5743563060202534,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1533,"name":"Otto Barten","entity_type":"person","category":"Organizer","definition":"Human-level artificial intelligence (AGI) that can perform cognitive tasks as well as humans","citation":"Otto Barten (director of ERO) gave a short introduction about existential risks, in particular those of human-level artificial intelligence (AGI), in front of a sold-out large hall. Large language models such as ChatGPT and Bing Chat suddenly seem to bring a future with AGI closer. Is that really so? And what happens if AI can perform any cognitive task as well as we can?","source_id":"src-8609188fb23b","date":"2023-04-25","confidence":"high","x":1.777359540976215,"y":7.409747264364074,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1537,"name":"Nik Samoylov","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"The type of AI that has capacity, at a minimum, to replace most people in their jobs","citation":"Over the past few days rumours rolled across the internet that OpenAI achieved AGI (artificial general intelligence). The type of AI that has capacity, at a minimum, to replace most people in their jobs.","source_id":"src-618b659c5374","date":"2023-11-18","confidence":"high","x":0.12110617473327943,"y":1.8742129359774407,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":1547,"name":"David Duvenaud","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI defined as matching the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult, grounded in Cattell-Horn-Carroll theory with ten core cognitive domains including reasoning, memory, and perception","citation":"The lack of a concrete definition for Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) obscures the gap between today's specialized AI and human-level cognition. This paper introduces a quantifiable framework to address this, defining AGI as matching the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult.","source_id":"src-ae10edde5b02","date":"2025-10-20","confidence":"high","x":1.245932547564359,"y":9.209426937315296,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1548,"name":"Roger Grosse","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI as systems with 'rapid progress in capabilities' that could 'learn potentially catastrophic capabilities,' implying AGI is characterized by broad, advanced capability acquisition that poses serious safety challenges.","citation":"With the rapid progress in AGI capabilities, AGI systems will learn potentially catastrophic capabilities, and developers will need to be able to demonstrate their safety.","source_id":"src-98d836d6aaa0","date":"2024-12-10","confidence":"low","x":0.14254402623368706,"y":7.081306677335185,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":1557,"name":"Lila Ibrahim","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AGI is versatile AI that equals humans in all cognitive abilities and can act as a personal assistant with broad world understanding, context awareness, and memory.","citation":"Unser Ziel bei Deepmind ist schon immer gewesen, eine allgemeine künstliche Intelligenz zu entwickeln, die alles kann, was Menschen können... Aber wir wollen wirklich vielseitige KI bauen, die in allen kognitiven Fähigkeiten dem Menschen ebenbürtig ist. Dafür sind noch ein paar Durchbrüche nötig.","source_id":"src-9620c0b20f4a","date":"2026-01-23","confidence":"high","x":1.0332458738579553,"y":8.6031871025205,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1563,"name":"Emmett Shear","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AGI requires open-ended continual learning and reflective theory of mind - the capacity to understand oneself and one's own learning process.","citation":"I think that AGI and alignment are the same problem. If you have a general intelligence, it is necessarily capable of open ended continual learning. And the most difficult, challenging intellectual problem there is, reflective theory of mind.","source_id":"src-b89dbe87b2fa","date":"2025-12-19","confidence":"high","x":0.24192064169911065,"y":8.151702505126503,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":1567,"name":"Steve Omohundro","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"Artificial General Intelligence with thinking ability comparable to humans, implementing both rapid decision making (System 1) and slower deliberative reasoning (System 2)","citation":"The leading AI labs all aim to develop 'Artificial General Intelligence (AGI)' with a thinking ability comparable to humans. Cognitive psychologists identify two distinct human systems for cognition: 'System 1' implements rapid decision making and 'System 2' implements slower deliberative reasoning. Today's LLMs primarily mimic the human System 1 and the AI labs hope that improved agentic harnesses will unlock System 2 deliberative reasoning.","source_id":"src-9997ccb63855","date":"2025-07-23","confidence":"high","x":1.0532925998430063,"y":3.3310278755828002,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1585,"name":"Jaime Sevilla","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AI that can substitute for humans in scientific endeavors and take over scientific and technological progress from humans.","citation":"Daniel Filan (01:16:55): I want to talk a little bit more about what you can say about AGI: AI that can take over scientific and technological progress from humans. [...] Jaime Sevilla (01:17:23): It's going to be somewhere in there you get the required level of compute to make AI that can substitute for humans in scientific endeavors a reality.","source_id":"src-94ab279e43a8","date":"2024-10-03","confidence":"high","x":0.09777186304811517,"y":2.2448241759885725,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"autonomous-research-capability","cluster_label":"Autonomous Research"},{"entity_id":1586,"name":"Tamay Besiroglu","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is a system capable of fully automating economically meaningful work across diverse real-world tasks, including long-horizon agency, multimodal capabilities, and novel problem-solving in environments without prior training data — not merely narrow task performance.","citation":"I think something that would reveal its ability to do very long context things, use multimodal capabilities in a meaningful way, and integrate that with reasoning and other types of systems. And also agency and being able to take action over a long horizon and accomplish some tasks that takes very long for humans to do, not just in specific software environments, but just very broadly; say downloading an arbitrary game from Steam, something that it's never seen before, it doesn't really have much training data, maybe it was released after a training cutoff and so there's no tutorials... and then accomplishing that game and actually playing that game to the end.","source_id":"src-6c178a1c6281","date":"2025-04-16","confidence":"medium","x":-0.40423089372529414,"y":6.346059274307161,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":1588,"name":"Lennart Heim","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI, transformative AI, or human-level AI definitions vary and people should specify what they mean rather than just giving timeline predictions","citation":"I think it's really important for people to actually say what they mean with these kinds of terms, and not just say like, oh, my AGI timelines are X, Y, Z... I do think I have a 50% chance, within the next 20 years or so, there might be something what we might call an AGI or transformative AI. What do I mean by this?","source_id":"src-0a8516cb7d1c","date":"2024-04-30","confidence":"medium","x":1.280134814436629,"y":8.070767852859964,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1590,"name":"Tom Davidson","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AI that can do 100% of cognitive tasks at least as well as the best humans can","citation":"Developing artificial general intelligence (AGI) — AI that can do 100% of cognitive tasks at least as well as the best humans can — could very easily lead us to an unrecognisable world.","source_id":"src-9a8fd425d7f1","date":"2023-05-04","confidence":"high","x":0.7904454152733212,"y":2.433528105988233,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1594,"name":"Jesse Clifton","entity_type":"person","category":"Organizer","definition":"AGI as a strategic agent capable of making commitments and engaging in conflict, operating in multipolar deployment scenarios with goals that may or may not align with human values.","citation":"To avoid catastrophic conflict in multipolar AI scenarios, we would like to design AI systems such that AI-enabled actors will tend to cooperate. This post is about some problems facing this effort and some possible solutions. To explain these problems, I'll take the view that the agents deployed by AI...","source_id":"src-d47ff5046d99","date":"2020-04-01","confidence":"low","x":0.1646336191925745,"y":7.4456584200064135,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":1597,"name":"Founders Pledge","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"Uses 'Advanced Artificial Intelligence' as effectively the same as 'Transformative AI' (TAI) but intentionally avoids being too prescriptive with definitions.","citation":"I'm somewhat loose with definitions here, defining it effectively the same way as 'Transformative AI' (TAI) but intentionally not being too prescriptive for the most part (except in cases where definitions become important).","source_id":"src-da07b0dae774","date":"2024-06-20","confidence":"high","x":-1.9924507132029927,"y":7.750854761028034,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1605,"name":"Allison Duettmann","entity_type":"person","category":"Organizer","definition":"AGI is treated as a distinct and important milestone requiring coordination, safety work, and governance; the report references a companion document 'AGI Safety: Overview & Definitions' for precise definitions, acknowledging that different researchers use varying terms for AI, AGI, and Superintelligence.","citation":"For an overview of different AI definitions, including AI, AGI, and Superintelligence, see AGI Safety: Overview & Definitions (Duettmann, 2018). A widely accepted definition of AI-related concepts or clarifications in which definitions are used in a given context could enhance useful policy development and coordination by avoiding unnecessary confusion and miscommunication.","source_id":"src-6919b848d56b","date":"2023-01-05","confidence":"medium","x":-1.4470804433633244,"y":8.488783120991108,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"10-25 years","timeline_score":4,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1625,"name":"Siméon Campos","entity_type":"person","category":"Organizer","definition":"AGI is defined as an AI which is capable of having all the capabilities and particular reasoning capabilities that humans have","citation":"AGI usually when people talk about it, is defined as an AI which is capable of having all the capabilities and particular reasoning capabilities that human have. [...] I think that the part of general which refers to modality is not very interesting because it's not what matters. Everything that make human much more powerful than other animals is nothing physical, not even just their ability to build things and to reason and to have conceptual views on the world.","source_id":"src-5132e2676dba","date":"2023-04-28","confidence":"high","x":-0.00361702474944132,"y":8.12577508969083,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1626,"name":"Henry Papadatos","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AGI traditionally meant machines that think, learn, and adapt like humans, but questions whether this anthropomorphic view makes sense given our limited understanding of human intelligence itself.","citation":"The term AGI made sense from far away, when AI systems were very narrow. Now we have systems that are quite general already and the term does not mean as much.","source_id":"src-b3a84ce7beca","date":"2026-01-15","confidence":"high","x":-0.08110291987469778,"y":8.20716307892875,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1658,"name":"William MacAskill","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"An AI system, or collection of systems, that is capable of doing essentially all economically useful tasks that human beings can do and doing so more cheaply than the relevant humans at any level of expertise.","citation":"By \"AGI\" I mean an AI system, or collection of systems, that is capable of doing essentially all economically useful tasks that human beings can do and doing so more cheaply than the relevant humans at any level of expertise. (This is a much higher bar than some people mean when they say \"AGI\".)","source_id":"src-ebf5bbed6851","date":"2026-01-27","confidence":"high","x":0.003172596262471168,"y":2.1146619386510905,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"2-3 years","timeline_score":2,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":1660,"name":"Andrea Miotti","entity_type":"person","category":"Organizer","definition":"There already are general AIs that are not powerful enough yet to count as True AGIs","citation":"The Race for powerful AGIs has already started. There already are general AIs. They just are not powerful enough yet to count as True AGIs.","source_id":"src-a5550b3a3fc4","date":"2023-02-01","confidence":"medium","x":1.6757933651097987,"y":8.21660247311078,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1662,"name":"Adam Shimi","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is defined as when AI can do all tasks a human can on a computer and conduct AI research itself.","citation":"At the point when AI is able to do all of the tasks a human can on a computer, it will functionally be AGI and able to conduct the same AI research that we can. Should this happen, AGI will quickly scale to superintelligence, and then to levels so powerful that AI is best described as a god compared to humans.","source_id":"src-d11b78235d2c","date":"2024-10-31","confidence":"high","x":-0.8549517626840383,"y":8.168668469000385,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1663,"name":"Adam Gleave","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"Gleave uses a three-tier framework: (1) systems useful for specific tasks but not generally autonomous; (2) systems that can autonomously complete meaningful long-horizon tasks (roughly equivalent to common 'AGI' usage); and (3) systems that can autonomously outcompete well-run human-plus-AI organizations across domains, which he considers the most transformative threshold.","citation":"People often mean radically different things even by the same term, like AGI. So I distinguish maybe three qualitatively different levels of development, each of which have pretty significant implications in terms of how a technology is going to transform the world and how you'd need to regulate or respond to it.","source_id":"src-50d6ddbfa90a","date":"2025-09-19","confidence":"high","x":-1.0777026004988028,"y":7.204400265673953,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":1666,"name":"Marc Warner","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AGI is a system that mimics human intelligence across various tasks; it does not yet exist but technologies like GPT-4 are a step in that direction.","citation":"Conversely, general AI systems – which mimic human intelligence across various tasks – are far more risky and less defined. Artificial general intelligence (AGI) doesn't exist yet but technologies like GPT4 are a step in that direction.","source_id":"src-7b755328f0f8","date":"2024-09-30","confidence":"high","x":-0.1684434180952843,"y":7.808316139490143,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1669,"name":"Remmelt Ellen","entity_type":"person","category":"Organizer","definition":"Self-learning and self-maintaining machinery that can adapt to changes within complex environments","citation":"Does how we are able to manage current software and hardware systems to operate correspond soundly with how self-learning and self-maintaining machinery ('AGI') contr...","source_id":"src-a1447b10e186","date":"2024-05-03","confidence":"medium","x":-0.2733994386751861,"y":4.537642451174078,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":1674,"name":"Vincent Conitzer","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AI that is to us in cognitive abilities (roughly) as we are to ants","citation":"superintelligent AI – by which I mean the kind of AI that is to us in cognitive abilities (roughly) as we are to ants.","source_id":"src-4b50009d7609","date":"2025-08-22","confidence":"high","x":0.8503088830422614,"y":2.625635977703431,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":1676,"name":"Jan Kulveit","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AI transition occurs when AI systems overtake humans as the most powerful actors, happening across multiple domains with cyborg periods where human+AI teams outperform both humans alone and AIs alone","citation":"Looking at all of human history, it might make sense to think of ourselves as at the cusp of an AI transition, when AI systems overtake humans as the most powerful actors.","source_id":"src-5ac5c869d203","date":"2025-05-06","confidence":"high","x":0.20735018225162916,"y":2.2502389888307492,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":1683,"name":"Peter Wildeford","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"An AGI system that can replace 99% of all current remote worker jobs in a cost-competitive way","citation":"Maybe an AGI system can replace, say, 99% of all current remote worker jobs as of today, March 11th, 2025. And, yeah, I guess you might have a question about whether there will be new jobs that humans can do—and I guess let's also say the AGI has to do this in a cost-competitive way.","source_id":"src-09901b7ab2a9","date":"2025-03-19","confidence":"high","x":0.02443732940258327,"y":6.05581555178699,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":1690,"name":"Connor Axiotes","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AGI systems with superhuman labour abilities, generality across all human tasks, and agency to plan and execute their own objectives.","citation":"I am pretty confident that future AGI systems will have superhuman labour abilities, generality, and agency.","source_id":"src-6c2dce62e5b8","date":"2023-05-03","confidence":"high","x":-0.06319967045657543,"y":6.44364920419763,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"5-10 years","timeline_score":3,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":1722,"name":"Arthur Mensch","entity_type":"person","category":"Executive","definition":"AGI is an aspirational 'north star' concept representing continuous system improvement, not a singular abstraction capable of solving the complexity of real enterprise systems.","citation":"\"In real life, enterprises are complex systems, and you can't solve that with a single abstraction like AGI. AGI, to a large extent, is a north star of 'I'm going to make the system better over time.'\" – Arthur Mensch – Mistral CEO","source_id":"src-9c2b73c900e7","date":"2026-01-16","confidence":"high","x":-0.7474574091170799,"y":9.224319031189149,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Ill-defined","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Overstated","risk_score":1,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1741,"name":"Scott Aaronson","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is an AI that can match or exceed the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult","citation":"AGI is an AI that can match or exceed the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult.","source_id":"src-5279448b108b","date":"2025-10-20","confidence":"high","x":1.3029424178126248,"y":9.20225251886866,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1744,"name":"Anca Dragan","entity_type":"person","category":"Academic","definition":"AGI is understood as an advanced AI system that must be aligned with human values and goals; the core challenge is ensuring such systems pursue intended human objectives rather than misaligned proxies.","citation":"\"For AGI to truly complement human abilities, it has to be aligned with human values. Misalignment occurs when the AI system pursues a goal that is different from human intentions.\"","source_id":"src-cedad15781bf","date":"2025-04-01","confidence":"high","x":-0.2630417889175741,"y":7.458155183017308,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"conceptual-critique","cluster_label":"Conceptual Critique"},{"entity_id":1748,"name":"Gabriel Alfour","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is defined as an AI that can match or exceed the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult.","citation":"AGI is an AI that can match or exceed the cognitive versatility and proficiency of a well-educated adult.","source_id":"src-6233799b8c55","date":"2025-12-03","confidence":"high","x":1.2077487022487698,"y":9.242528986429598,"stance":"Precautionary","stance_score":6,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1767,"name":"Daniel Colson","entity_type":"person","category":"Organizer","definition":"AGI is framed as an impending technological development with enormous risk potential, serious enough that Silicon Valley takes it seriously and Washington should too.","citation":"Artificial generative intelligence is no longer a distant speculation—it's an impending reality that carries enormous risk.","source_id":"src-f228de8cfd34","date":"2024-10-17","confidence":"low","x":-0.615480429057598,"y":9.158375219230923,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Catastrophic","risk_score":4,"cluster_id":"transformative-societal-impact","cluster_label":"Transformative Impact"},{"entity_id":1768,"name":"Brad Carson","entity_type":"person","category":"Organizer","definition":"AI that promises to automate all cognitive labor and can do everything a human can do","citation":"A technology that promises to automate all cognitive labor. And if that does happen, and this is the stated ambition of the frontier AI labs to, to basically create an AI that can do everything a human can do is going to only affect our jobs, of course. It's going to affect the entire social contract.","source_id":"src-eeb1b041dcc0","date":"2025-12-08","confidence":"medium","x":1.5489586164781293,"y":2.4259365581468684,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"economic-automation","cluster_label":"Economic Work Automation"},{"entity_id":1770,"name":"Information Technology Industry Council","entity_type":"organization","category":"Think Tank/Policy Org","definition":"Agentic AI as a system with multi-step planning and reasoning capabilities that can autonomously query and select tools within boundaries set by the user to execute on a user-defined task or achieve an outcome.","citation":"We define agentic AI as a system with multi-step planning and reasoning capabilities that can autonomously query and select tools within boundaries set by the user to execute on a user-defined task or achieve an outcome.","source_id":"src-5ffa04b37c86","date":"2025-11-07","confidence":"high","x":-0.4069826204895553,"y":5.664471139717956,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"general-purpose-agents","cluster_label":"General-Purpose Agents"},{"entity_id":1771,"name":"Viktoriya Krakovna","entity_type":"person","category":"Researcher","definition":"AGI is a hypothetical, general AI system that would be able to do anything a human can do, or perform the vast majority of tasks that humans can perform, distinct from narrow AI systems that perform specific tasks or handle specific domains.","citation":"AGI is stands for Artificial General Intelligence. It's a hypothetical, general AI system that would be able to do anything a human can do, or perform the vast majority of tasks that humans can perform. Which is distinct from the current AI systems that we have now, which are called narrow AI systems that perform specific tasks or that can handle specific domains, but cannot do everything a human can do.","source_id":"src-0f2c7fcce915","date":"2023-01-12","confidence":"high","x":0.7493343002800114,"y":7.514774994435259,"stance":"Moderate","stance_score":4,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1772,"name":"Anthony Aguirre","entity_type":"person","category":"Organizer","definition":"Full AGI defined as superhuman general-purpose AI that performs essentially all human cognitive tasks at or above top human expert level, combining high Autonomy, high Generality, and high Intelligence (A-G-I).","citation":"We'll define 'full' AGI to be synonymous with 'super-human general-purpose AI' meaning an AI system that is able to perform essentially all human cognitive tasks at or above top human expert level, as well as acquire new skills and transfer capability to new domains.","source_id":"src-06f8ed43b9e8","date":"2025-03-05","confidence":"high","x":0.14828909885247143,"y":7.170286593133587,"stance":"Restrictive","stance_score":5,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Existential","risk_score":5,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"},{"entity_id":1774,"name":"Department for Science, Innovation and Technology","entity_type":"organization","category":"Government/Agency","definition":"AI that can complete almost any task at or above human levels","citation":"The definition of artificial general intelligence (AGI) is contested, but the term is used by Kyle's Department for Science, Innovation and Technology (DSIT) to refer to AI that can complete almost any task at or above human levels.","source_id":"src-48813f4053d5","date":"2025-09-03","confidence":"high","x":1.5876331997267195,"y":2.6521915679472,"stance":"Light-touch","stance_score":2,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Manageable","risk_score":2,"cluster_id":"human-level-cognitive-parity","cluster_label":"Human-Level Cognitive Parity"},{"entity_id":1780,"name":"Adam Conner","entity_type":"person","category":"Organizer","definition":"AGI is an AI that has human-like intelligence and skills, representing a key step reached through recursive self-improvement, which would make human intelligence abundant with profound implications for the economy and democracy.","citation":"RSI means that AI models could self-train to even greater improvement, a key step along the path to what is known as Artificial General Intelligence, also called AGI, which describes an AI that has human-like intelligence and skills.","source_id":"src-95795ae6edbc","date":"2026-04-05","confidence":"high","x":-0.011069295321975339,"y":8.138117723504628,"stance":"Targeted","stance_score":3,"timeline":"Unknown","timeline_score":null,"risk":"Serious","risk_score":3,"cluster_id":"superintelligent-systems","cluster_label":"Superintelligent Systems"}],"sources":{"src-a0f96844580d":{"url":"https://c4dt.epfl.ch/pick/machines-of-loving-grace","title":"Dario Amodei — Machines of Loving Grace","type":"paper","date":"2024-07-07"},"src-dcef2577afc3":{"url":"https://doi.org/10.59350/redasadki.21109","title":"San Francisco Consensus: A New Epoch in AI","type":"report","date":"2025-07-15"},"src-32321a223aca":{"url":"https://futureoflife.org/project/the-windfall-trust/","title":"The Windfall Trust - Future of Life Institute","type":"report","date":"2024-02-14"},"src-889a9071c9dc":{"url":"https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/prm7jJMZzToZ4QxoK/the-compendium-a-full-argument-about-extinction-risk-from","title":"The Compendium, A full argument about extinction risk from AGI","type":"blog","date":"2024-10-31"},"src-2ae2cdf7193b":{"url":"https://www.acm.org/binaries/content/assets/public-policy/acm---ustpc-comments-on-ai-action-plan-final-submitted.pdf","title":"Comments on US AI Action Plan","type":"report","date":"2025-03-14"},"src-3d15c7f1bd55":{"url":"https://ae.studio/essays/a-reinforcement-learning-paradigm-guaranteed-to-achieve-human-level-